re preserved in the issue worktree; and `/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1292-e65093ea/script_run_metrics/` contains only aggregate `add_new_library_support.json` and `fix_javac_fail.json`, with no issue-specific or `fails-java-run` metrics.\\n\\nNo matching run logs were preserved for this library/version. The only issue-specific path currently present is `/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_1292.log`, and there are no corresponding issue-specific entries under `/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/logs/metadata-fix/`, `/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/logs/populate-artifact-urls/`, or `/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/logs/checkstyle/` for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Re-run the `fails-java-run` workflow for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30` with log retention enabled, or reproduce locally with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` to capture the first failing Gradle task.\\n2. Inspect the fresh run’s Gradle/test logs and scratch metrics immediately after failure, because this preserved run did not retain any actionable `1.5.30` generation artifacts.\\n3. If the rerun still fails, manually scaffold the `1.5.30` test/metadata from the latest existing `logback-classic` entry and debug the runtime failure from the reproduced output.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T17:01:56Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1292#issuecomment-4328916591\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAjIDMg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1292-fails-java-run-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.30-1f870a68.\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: the `fix-java-run-fail` loop failed in the JVM `:test` / `:tckTest` step. In `logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-44-37-577278Z.log`, `ClassicVersionUtilTest > packageScopedVersionLookupReadsResourceBesideSuppliedClass()` fails with `expected: \\\"1.5.30\\\" but was: null`, which then causes `:test FAILED` and `:tckTest FAILED` with `Test for ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 failed with exit code 1`.\\n\\nThe preserved work looks useful, but the workflow appears to have stopped before a clean verified handoff. The same PI log shows the agent amending `ClassicVersionUtilTest` and then reporting `I did not rerun the tests`, while `git status` still showed `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/index.json` modified and `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/reachability-metadata.json` untracked. Metrics still completed 12 iterations and ended at commit `d1dce47332e0305073c478ad23f56e4c0d3716bc`, which adds the generated metadata/index/stats updates. A later local verification in `logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows both `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` passing.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-44-37-577278Z.log`\\n- `logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-41-09-576397Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and verify that the `ClassicVersionUtilTest` fix and the metadata/index/stats changes from `d1dce47332` are all present together.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30`.\\n3. If both lanes pass, open a normal PR from the preserved branch; if not, continue debugging from that branch, starting with the `ClassicVersionUtilTest` resource lookup path and the new `reachability-metadata.json`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T01:58:45Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1292#issuecomment-4331799346\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAme-mQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed (`fails-java-run`, workflow status `failure`, reason `job_failed`), but preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1292-fails-java-run-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.30-4ca5ae2b\\n\\nThe most likely failure was after the actual Java-run fix was generated, during the later coverage/finalization part of the workflow rather than in the underlying `logback-classic` fix itself. In `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T11-56-56-901056Z.log`, the preserved run identifies the concrete runtime issue for `1.5.30` (`LoggerFactory.getILoggerFactory()` returning SLF4J NOP instead of a Logback `LoggerContext` in this setup), updates the tests to initialize `LogbackServiceProvider` directly, and then reports both `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` as successful, with `76` tests successful. The preserved branch head also contains generated metadata and stats; `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/stats.json` reports dynamic-access coverage at `17/17`, and the generated JVM test results under `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/build/test-results/test/` show zero failures, including `TEST-org.graalvm.logback.LogbackTests.xml` with `tests=\\\"76\\\" failures=\\\"0\\\" errors=\\\"0\\\"`.\\n\\nWhat appears to have gone wrong is that later iterative logs, especially `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T12-23-20-246059Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T12-26-15-863099Z.log`, add follow-up coverage commits but end with “Per instruction, I did not compile or run tests”, so the final preserved head was likely not revalidated before the workflow terminated. `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/metadata-fix/codex.log` is also worth checking because it captures the earlier successful `./gradlew test` execution from the metadata-fix side.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30` on the branch head.\\n2. If the branch head does not validate cleanly, compare it with the earlier validated state described in `pi-generation-2026-04-28T11-56-56-901056Z.log` and keep only the verified commits needed for `1.5.30`.\\n3. If the preserved branch validates, use it as the basis for the manual follow-up PR or retrigger the workflow from that branch.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T12:43:13Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1292#issuecomment-4335320729\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDuxsA\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1292-fails-java-run-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.30-596eb878\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the JVM `:test` task reached during `:tckTest`/`nativeTest`, before the automation could produce a fix. In `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T10-48-32-796408Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-44-51-831061Z.log`, `LogbackTests > initializationError FAILED` ends with `java.lang.ClassCastException: org.slf4j.helpers.NOPLoggerFactory cannot be cast to ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext` at `org.graalvm.logback.LogbackTests.<clinit>(LogbackTests.java:55)`. The run metrics in `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/execution-metrics.json` show `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_file: None`, and no commit change, so the job stopped without generating a candidate patch.\\n\\nThere is also a follow-on native verification failure worth checking after the JVM issue is fixed. `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T10-48-57-046228Z.log` shows `MissingResourceRegistrationError: Cannot access resource at path 'META-INF/services/javax.xml.stream.XMLOutputFactory'`, and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-48-32-818051Z.log` shows 5 native test failures (`patternLayout`, `xmlLayout`, `consoleAppenderPropertySetter`, `testFileAppender`, `testRollingFileAppender`).\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Reproduce and fix the JVM test initialization problem around SLF4J/logback binding in `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/src/test/java/org/graalvm/logback/LogbackTests.java` so `LoggerFactory.getILoggerFactory()` does not resolve to `NOPLoggerFactory`.\\n2. Rerun the 1.5.30 TCK after that fix and inspect the native follow-up failures, especially the missing `META-INF/services/javax.xml.stream.XMLOutputFactory` resource and the 5 failing native assertions/file-appender checks.\\n3. Continue from the preserved branch above if manual fixes are needed.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T10:50:54Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1292#issuecomment-4365988272\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T13:12:54Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0olA\",\"name\":\"fails-java-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail during java testing\",\"color\":\"8f51c9\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":1292,\"title\":\"[Automation] java run fails for ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T10:51:00Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1292\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/4262.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MjcwMzI1\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"graalvmbot\",\"name\":\"graalvm bot\"},\"body\":\"## java run on ubuntu-latest / JDK 25 / mode current-defaults\\n\\nFailure kind: java run\\nOS: ubuntu-latest\\nJDK: 25\\nNative-image mode: current-defaul