 referenced metrics commits (`5e7e67431f7c4999d9381fe68b11e0e048c88e87` and `2de9986be4625f53dea190c96e3e4a55a936cd4a`) are not present here, and no matching run logs were found.\\n\\nPlease inspect `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json`, `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/stats.json`, and the run-log locations `forge/script_run_metrics/` and `forge/benchmark_run_metrics/` in the scratch metrics repo for the missing failure context.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Verify whether this issue is already resolved by commit `d5d31dfcda` (`[GenAI] Test fix for org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0 using gpt-5.5 (#4229)`) and close it if the failure was stale.\\n- Check the original workflow run outside this worktree to find the missing job logs and why the recorded commits were not preserved onto the human-intervention branch.\\n- If follow-up is still needed, recreate a branch from the existing generated files under `tests/src/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0` and `metadata/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0` and rerun the handoff manually.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T10:24:01Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4262#issuecomment-4363584577\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBBljcg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0`, but the retained artifacts suggest the failure happened after the Java-run repair itself. `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json` records `fix_java_run_fail:2026-05-02` with status `success`, a generated test at `tests/src/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/src/test/java/org_apache_thrift/libthrift/TSSLTransportFactoryTest.java`, and dynamic-access coverage `9/9`. The `libthrift:0.17.0` changes are already on `master` in commit `d5d31dfcda` (`[GenAI] Test fix for org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0 using gpt-5.5 (#4229)`), and the preserved work branch points at that same state: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4262-fails-java-run-org.apache.thrift-libthrift-0.17.0-0b51557d\\n\\nI could not find matching Gradle/JUnit run logs, test `build/` outputs, or `forge/.pending_metrics.json` in this worktree, so the most likely failing stage is post-run orchestration/preservation or issue bookkeeping rather than the `javaTest` repair loop itself. The only retained issue-specific log path I found is `forge/logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_4262.log`; maintainers should also inspect `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json` and the generated test project under `tests/src/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Verify whether issue `#4262` is stale or duplicate of the already-merged fix in commit `d5d31dfcda` / PR `#4229`, and close or relabel it if appropriate.\\n- Check the workflow/job history around branch preservation and comment posting to see why the run ended as `job_failed` despite successful `fix_java_run_fail` metrics.\\n- If the failure is still reproducible, rerun `javaTest` for `org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0` and retain the missing Gradle/JUnit logs in the preserved branch.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T12:04:12Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4262#issuecomment-4363740018\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBB_Ssw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4262-fails-java-run-org.apache.thrift-libthrift-0.17.0-78318ac7\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the `fix-java-run-fail` handoff/metrics path, not the actual Java/native test stage. `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-40-55-726491Z.log` ends with “No code changes were needed” and says the runtime failure could not be reproduced. Both `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-39-49-909660Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-40-55-730723Z.log` end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and “Test for org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0 passed”, `tests/src/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` reports 6 tests with 0 failures/errors, and `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/stats.json` shows dynamic-access coverage 9/9. In contrast, `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json` was rewritten to `status: failure` with `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, `artifacts.metadata_file: None`, and the same starting/ending commit (`cec4502ff46f042ec486c613e51dd2b022d85122`), which points to stale/misclassified bookkeeping after a passing verification run. The preserved branch also only adds log/test-result artifacts and the rewritten metrics file relative to `master`; it does not contain new test or metadata source changes for this coordinate.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-40-55-726491Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-39-49-909660Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-40-55-730723Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T15-40-58-066345Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Confirm whether this issue is stale/misclassified, since the preserved run shows passing `test` and `nativeTest` for `org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0`.\\n- Inspect why `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json` was rewritten to failure despite the passing logs and native test report.\\n- If a clean reproduction is still needed, rerun from a commit before the existing `libthrift:0.17.0` test/metadata landed rather than from the current `master`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T15:43:17Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4262#issuecomment-4364161715\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDocAw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4262-fails-java-run-org.apache.thrift-libthrift-0.17.0-8c4d4454\\n\\nThe preserved artifacts suggest the failing stage in this run is most likely the native trace verification step, not the Java test run itself. `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T09-45-53-462701Z.log` shows `nativeTest` finishing successfully with 6 tests successful / 0 failed, and `tests/src/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` also reports 6 tests and 0 failures. The concrete failure appears in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T09-46-09-852238Z.log`, where `runNativeTraceImage` throws `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.resources.MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`.\\n\\nThe automation also did not make any new fix attempt in this run: `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T09-45-53-447427Z.log` ends with “No code changes were made,” and `stats/org.apache.thrift/libthrift/0.17.0/execution-metrics.json` shows the 2026-05-03 run failed after 1 iteration with `generated_loc: 0` and identical starting/ending commits.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T09-46-09-852238Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T09-45-53-462701Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T09-45-53-447427Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Reproduce `runNativeTraceImage` for `org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0` and identify which metadata source should register `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`.\\n2. Verify whether this is a TCK/JUnit test-harness metadata problem rather than a `libthrift` Java runtime problem, since the generated tests already pass.\\n3. After fixing the missing resource registration in the appropriate place, rerun the `fails-java-run` workflow for this library.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T09:47:54Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4262#issuecomment-4365884419\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T09:47:33Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0olA\",\"name\":\"fails-java-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail during java testing\",\"color\":\"8f51c9\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":4262,\"title\":\"[Automation] java run fails for org.apache.thrift:libthrift:0.17.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T09:47:59Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4262\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/2856.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.osgi:core:4.3.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBC2ArQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.osgi:core:4.3.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2856-library-new-request-org.osgi-core-4.3.0-22949cc2\\n\\nMost likely failure stage: test generation / native verification. The run metrics ended with `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the starting and ending commit stayed at `c6a2645689c43dbf0094d5b99f8a701df6bb37f4` (`stats/org.osgi/core/4.3.0/execution-metrics.json`), even though the dynamic-access report shows `5/11` covered calls (45.45%) in `tests/src/org.osgi/core/4.3.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`. The native test run then failed in `FrameworkUtilInnerFilterImplTest`: `matchesComparableValuesUsingStringConstructorConversion()` and `matchesUnknownValuesUsingStringConstructorConversion()` both failed with `Expecting value to be true but was false`, and `:nativeTest FAILED` (`human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:core:4.3.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T00-43-03-150770Z.log`). Native trace verification also reported `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter` during `runNativeTraceImage` (`human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:core:4.3.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T00-43-37-913309Z.log`).\\n\\nPaths to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:core:4.3.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T00-43-03-141775Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:core:4.3.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T00-43-03-150770Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:core:4.3.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T00-43-37-913309Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.osgi/core/4.3.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n- `tests/src/org.osgi/core/4.3.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\n1. Recover or recreate the intended `FrameworkUtilInnerFilterImplTest` from the preserved branch/build outputs and fix the two failing native assertions.\\n2. Decide whether `runNativeTraceImage` needs additional test-only resource metadata for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter` or whether the verification step should be adjusted.\\n3. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.osgi:core:4.3.0` and confirm dynamic-access coverage improves beyond `5/11` so the new-library coverage gate is met.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T00:45:23Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2856#issuecomment-4365058221\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEejsQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed before it produced a preserved diff or any run-specific logs/metrics. The preserved work branch is https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2856-library-new-request-org.osgi-core-4.3.0-b245534b, but it points to the same commit as `master`, and there are no files under `forge/script_run_metrics/` or `forge/benchmark_run_metrics/`. That makes the most likely failing stage test generation / coordinate resolution, not later Gradle test execution.\\n\\nConcrete evidence: this repository already contains support for `org.osgi:org.osgi.core:4.3.0`, including `metadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/reachability-metadata.json`, `tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/`, `stats/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/execution-metrics.json`, and `stats/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/stats.json`; `metadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/index.json` already lists `4.3.0` as a tested version. There is no corresponding `metadata/tests/stats` tree for `org.osgi/core/4.3.0`, so the request likely used the wrong artifact coordinates (`org.osgi:core:4.3.0` instead of `org.osgi:org.osgi.core:4.3.0`) or retried an already-supported library. No matching run logs were found in the preserved worktree. For reference, the existing `stats/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/stats.json` shows prior dynamic-access coverage at 5/11 calls (45.45%), but this failed run did not emit its own stats.\\n\\nPlease inspect `metadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/index.json`, `tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/gradle.properties`, `stats/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/execution-metrics.json`, `stats/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/stats.json`, and confirm whether anything should have been written under `forge/script_run_metrics/` or `forge/benchmark_run_metrics/`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Verify the requested Maven coordinates; if the target was `org.osgi:org.osgi.core:4.3.0`, close this as already supported or rerun with the correct coordinates.\\n2. If `org.osgi:core:4.3.0` is intentional, reproduce generation locally for that exact coordinate and capture the first failing Gradle/task output, since no run logs were preserved here.\\n3. Check why the workflow preserved an empty branch with no metrics/log artifacts so future `test_generation_failed` cases leave actionable output.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T17:41:36Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2856#issuecomment-4366771121\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:28Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":2856,\"title\":\"Support for org.osgi:core:4.3.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T17:41:41Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2856\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/3899.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjc0Nzky\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"jkuipers\",\"name\":\"Joris Kuipers\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26\\nch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26\\n\\n### Additional context and logs\\n\\nStarting with [release 1.5.26](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/releases/tag/v_1.5.26), Logback has introduced new version properties files that are read at initialization time. When using a native image these files aren't available as resources, causing warnings during startup:\\n```\\n|-WARN in ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext[default] - Versions of logback-classic and ? are different or unknown.\\n```\\nThis is especially annoying because a single warning during Logback initialization will cause *all* of its internal startup logging to become visible, so this produces a lot of noise.\\n\\nFor logback-classic, the file that needs to be available as a resource is `ch/qos/logback/classic/logback-classic-version.properties`. For logback-core, it's `ch/qos/logback/core/logback-core-version.properties`. \\n\\n### GraalVM version\\n\\nNot relevant, but was a 25 version\\n\\n### Operating system\\n\\nLinux\\n\\n### CPU architecture\\n\\nAMD64 (x86-64)\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA7Jftw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26` (`library-update-request`, workflow status `failure`). Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3899-library-update-request-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.26-51f182a1\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the update/finalization path around artifact URL population for an already-covered version, not the underlying Gradle test execution. `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` shows `populateArtifactURLs` completed but reported `No matching coordinates found for filter 'ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26'`. In the repo, `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/index.json` already lists `1.5.26` under the `1.5.7` metadata entry with `test-version` `1.4.1`, and there is no `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/execution-metrics.json`. In the preserved local Gradle outputs, the existing `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.4.1` project ran `test` and `nativeTestCompile` successfully against the `1.5.26` JAR and produced a dynamic-access report with `4/18` covered calls, but that result was not recorded into stats. Please inspect `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` first, and if you check out the preserved worktree locally also inspect `build/tests/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/*.out`.\\n\\n1. Verify whether issue #3899 is stale or duplicate, since `1.5.26` is already present in `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/index.json`.\\n2. If coverage for `1.5.26` still needs to be refreshed, continue manually from the existing `1.4.1` test suite and write the missing stats/metadata update.\\n3. If the version is already sufficiently covered, close the issue or adjust the workflow so already-tested versions do not fail at `populateArtifactURLs`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T00:07:04Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4356988855\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA8_itQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"jkuipers\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"CONTRIBUTOR\",\"body\":\"I see that you've changed the title of the issue to only reference logback-classic: please note that this issue requires both logback-classic AND logback-core to be updated with their respective version properties file to address the issue. \",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T10:37:48Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":true,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4358922933\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA9LDXQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"> I see that you've changed the title of the issue to only reference logback-classic: please note that this issue requires both logback-classic AND logback-core to be updated with their respective version properties file to address the issue.\\n\\n@jkuipers I will open separate issue for logback-core. Thanks!\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T11:40:45Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4359111517\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA9ulAw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3899-library-new-request-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.26-72c30579\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test-generation validation for the new direct-module test suite, not artifact discovery. `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/execution-metrics.json` shows the generation strategy itself completed successfully (`status: success`, 3 iterations, 289 generated LOC), and the final generation logs say targeted tests passed but the full suite still failed in `sequenceNumberAndCallerDataAreAvailableOnLoggingEvents` and `siftingAppenderRoutesEventsByMdcValue` (`human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T14-03-35-021907Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T14-05-18-592200Z.log`). The generated reports confirm this: `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/build/test-results/test/TEST-ch_qos_logback.logback_classic.Logback_classicTest.xml` fails because caller data is empty, and `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` also shows `java.nio.file.NoSuchFileException` for `alpha.log` in the sifting-appender test.\\n\\nThere is also a validation-path mismatch: the coordinate-level Gradle outputs under `build/tests/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/*.out` are mostly running the existing `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.4.1` project against the `1.5.26` jar, while the generated `1.5.26` project has its own failing JVM/native reports. Dynamic-access coverage for the generated `1.5.26` project is still unavailable because `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` was not produced. For context, artifact discovery and URL population appear to have completed; inspect `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` alongside the generation logs above.\\n\\n1. Re-run or inspect the generated `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26` suite manually and fix or replace the failing `sequenceNumberAndCallerDataAreAvailableOnLoggingEvents` and `siftingAppenderRoutesEventsByMdcValue` tests.\\n2. Decide whether this library should keep the new direct-module `1.5.26` test project or continue using the existing `1.4.1` reuse path that already exercises the `1.5.26` jar.\\n3. After the test path is settled, regenerate dynamic-access coverage/stats for `1.5.26` and re-run validation.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T14:12:54Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4359693571\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDbV7A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26` with workflow status `failure`, so the `library-update-request` did not produce a PR-ready update.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3899-library-update-request-ch.qos.logback-logback-core-1.5.26-4a60f9f8\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation, before any generated library artifacts were written. Evidence in the preserved workspace is that the branch contains only an empty checkpoint commit with no file diff from `origin/master`, there is no generated `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.5.26`, `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.5.26`, or `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.5.26`, and the scratch metrics directories `forge/benchmark_run_metrics` and `forge/script_run_metrics` are empty. Dynamic-access coverage is therefore unavailable because no run metrics were preserved.\\n\\nLogs to inspect: `forge/logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_3899.log`. No matching run logs were found under `forge/logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26/` beyond that failure-analysis trace.\\n\\nRecommended manual next steps:\\n- Re-run generation for `ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26` with verbose Forge/Gradle logging so the first failing generation step is captured.\\n- Use the existing `1.2.12` Logback Core tests and metadata as the baseline to manually scaffold `1.5.26` if the sources/tests are still compatible.\\n- If the rerun fails again, attach the first failing Forge or Gradle log to this issue and continue from the preserved branch.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T07:38:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4365669868\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T15:04:08Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc7_VUq2\",\"name\":\"priority\",\"description\":\"This is a priority issue\",\"color\":\"ffffff\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPVjvyQ\",\"name\":\"library-update-request\",\"description\":\"The current metadata for a library does not work for the user.\",\"color\":\"593691\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":3899,\"title\":\"Update existing library: ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T07:38:14Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/2123.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MjcwMzI1\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"graalvmbot\",\"name\":\"graalvm bot\"},\"body\":\"## java run on ubuntu-latest / JDK 25 / mode current-defaults\\n\\nFailure kind: java run\\nOS: ubuntu-latest\\nJDK: 25\\nNative-image mode: current-defaults\\nReproducer: `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\"current-defaults\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"2.4.0.RC1\\\" ./gradlew clean javaTest -Pcoordinates=\\\"io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.2.19.Final\\\"`\\nRunner log: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/actions/runs/24918023510/job/72974026697\\nLast 300 lines of the log:\\n```console\\n\\nBUILD FAILED in 4s\\n11 actionable tasks: 3 executed, 8 up-to-date\\n❌ ERROR: 'native-image run' for 2.4.0.RC1 failed with exit code 1.\\nSOFT-FAIL[native-image run][2.4.0.RC1][GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\"current-defaults\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"2.4.0.RC1\\\" ./gradlew clean test -Pcoordinates=\\\"io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.2.19.Final\\\"]\\n========================================================================================\\n io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.2.19.Final:2.4.0.RC1 stage javac compile\\n========================================================================================\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:extractPluginRequests UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:generatePluginAdapters UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:compileJava UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:compileGroovy UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:compil