parser generator test and any index/metadata needed for `2.4.0.RC1` compatibility.\\n3. If `javaTest` passes locally, inspect the GitHub Actions runner log for the missing failure output and rerun the compatibility workflow, since the preserved branch and metrics did not capture the failing log.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T12:30:10Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2123#issuecomment-4335222436\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDsPEA\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2123-fails-java-run-io.undertow-undertow-parser-generator-2.4.0.RC1-741eef3c\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the JVM test run. In `human-intervention-logs/io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-22-11-610360Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-23-35-380064Z.log`, all 6 tests in `Undertow_parser_generatorTest` fail from `io.undertow.annotationprocessor.AbstractParserGenerator.createTokenizer(...)` because `org.jboss.classfilewriter.DefaultClassFactory` cannot initialize: `IllegalAccessException: module java.base does not open java.lang to unnamed module`. The agent did not produce a fix; `stats/io.undertow/undertow-parser-generator/2.4.0.RC1/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, and the starting/ending commit stayed at `78bfb4619b52e6947f8277af3e0f09b4ec657398`. Dynamic-access coverage is unavailable because `stats/io.undertow/undertow-parser-generator/2.4.0.RC1/stats.json` was not produced.\\n\\nThe fix attempt log to inspect is `human-intervention-logs/io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T10-23-35-370758Z.log`. There is also a secondary native-trace issue in `human-intervention-logs/io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T10-23-53-646611Z.log`: `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/javax.xml.stream.XMLOutputFactory` during JUnit XML report writing, but that verification run itself finished successfully and does not appear to be the original failing stage.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Reproduce with `./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1` and verify whether this version now requires an explicit JVM open such as `--add-opens java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` or another runtime adjustment for `jboss-classfilewriter`.\\n- Adapt the `undertow-parser-generator` test/setup for `2.4.0.RC1` so parser generation still runs meaningfully without the module-access failure, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.undertow:undertow-parser-generator:2.4.0.RC1`.\\n- After the Java lane passes, inspect the native-trace log above and decide whether the `XMLOutputFactory` service resource needs explicit metadata or a test-reporting adjustment.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T10:25:37Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2123#issuecomment-4365946640\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-25T01:20:27Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0olA\",\"name\":\"fails-java-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail durin