ility-metadata/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/build/reports/tests/test/index.html\\n\\n* Try:\\n> Run with --scan to generate a Build Scan (Powered by Develocity).\\n\\nDeprecated Gradle features were used in this build, making it incompatible with Gradle 10.\\n\\nYou can use '--warning-mode all' to show the individual deprecation warnings and determine if they come from your own scripts or plugins.\\n\\nFor more on this, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\n\\nBUILD FAILED in 3s\\n11 actionable tasks: 3 executed, 8 up-to-date\\n\\n> Task :javaTest-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.0.0.Final FAILED\\n\\n[Incubating] Problems report is available at: file:///home/runner/work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/graalvm-reachability-metadata/build/reports/problems/problems-report.html\\n\\nFAILURE: Build failed with an exception.\\n\\n* What went wrong:\\nExecution failed for task ':javaTest-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.0.0.Final'.\\n> Java tests failed\\n\\n* Try:\\n> Run with --stacktrace option to get the stack trace.\\n> Run with --info or --debug option to get more log output.\\n> Run with --scan to generate a Build Scan (Powered by Develocity).\\n> Get more help at https://help.gradle.org.\\n\\nDeprecated Gradle features were used in this build, making it incompatible with Gradle 10.\\n\\nYou can use '--warning-mode all' to show the individual deprecation warnings and determine if they come from your own scripts or plugins.\\n\\nFor more on this, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\n\\nBUILD FAILED in 5s\\n11 actionable tasks: 3 executed, 8 up-to-date\\nFAILED [java run][6.1.0.Final][GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"6.1.0.Final\\\" ./gradlew clean javaTest -Pcoordinates=\\\"org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.0.0.Final\\\"]\\n\\n```\\n\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAgBq0w\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-818-fails-java-run-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.1.0.Final-59aae9f7\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: the Java run/scaffolding step failed before the workflow produced any issue-specific artifacts. Evidence: the preserved branch is identical to `origin/master` with no diff, there are no generated `6.1.0.Final` files under `metadata/`, `tests/src/`, or `stats/`, and the scratch metrics repo has no entry for this library in `script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json` or `script_run_metrics/fix_javac_fail.json`. The repo’s existing Hibernate inventory also points to a coordinate mismatch around 6.1: `metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/index.json` only covers `5.6.14.Final` and `6.0.0.Final`, while `metadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/index.json` has `default-for: 6.1.*` with `6.1.1.Final`, and `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/6.1.1.Final/build.gradle` depends on `org.hibernate.orm:hibernate-core`.\\n\\nPaths a maintainer should inspect:\\n- Scratch metrics repo: `script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json`\\n- Scratch metrics repo: `script_run_metrics/fix_javac_fail.json`\\n- Current worktree: `metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/index.json`\\n- Current worktree: `metadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/index.json`\\n- Current worktree: `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/build.gradle`\\n- Current worktree: `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/6.1.1.Final/build.gradle`\\n- Current worktree: `stats/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/stats.json`\\n- Current worktree: `stats/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/6.1.1.Final/stats.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Confirm whether the intended coordinates are `org.hibernate.orm:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final` rather than `org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final`, and correct the issue/workflow input if needed.\\n2. Re-run the workflow with full job log retention, since no issue-specific local logs were preserved for this failure.\\n3. If the coordinates are correct, start from the existing `org.hibernate.orm` 6.1.x scaffold and reproduce the Java run locally to capture the actual failing stack trace.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T16:08:49Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/818#issuecomment-4328549075\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAiyxHw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-818-fails-java-run-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.1.0.Final-6897e168\\n\\nThe original Java-run problem appears to have been fixed on the preserved branch, but the workflow most likely failed later during post-generation/finalization. In `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-27T23-58-34-082678Z.log`, the run initially fails at `SessionFactoryOptionsBuilderTest.java:104` with `applySettings(Map<String,String>)` vs `Map<String,Object>`, but the same log later shows `Test for org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final passed.` The post-gen step then reports one remaining native-image failure in `StatefulPersistenceContextTest.serializesPopulatedPersistenceContextSections()` (`java.lang.Long.serialVersionUID`, then `ClassNotFoundException: org.hibernate.collection.spi.PersistentBag`) in `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-28T00-21-24-022825Z.log`. However, `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows that follow-up metadata was added and targeted verification passed with `62` tests, `0` failures, and `StatefulPersistenceContextTest` green; immediately after that, the log ends with `ERROR codex_core::session: failed to record rollout items: thread ... not found`. `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` shows the same session-recording error even though that Gradle step ends `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`. The run metrics are consistent with this: `success_with_intervention`, 9 iterations, ending at `fcbe6681a8bd2e2bad9b272fcf222b9a56efda35`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-27T23-58-34-082678Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-28T00-21-24-022825Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final --stacktrace` and `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final` on the preserved branch.\\n2. If those checks are green, open or recreate the PR from the preserved branch, since the library support itself appears fixed.\\n3. Investigate the `codex_core::session` / rollout-recording failure in the automation wrapper, since that is the most likely reason the workflow was marked `job_failed`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T00:28:30Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/818#issuecomment-4331450655\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAmmSpg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-818-fails-java-run-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.1.0.Final-5235c777\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the very start of the `fails-java-run` workflow, during coordinate/project preparation or the first `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final` run, before issue-specific artifacts were written. Concrete evidence: the preserved branch is identical to `master` and was created directly from `HEAD` with no preservation commit; there is no generated `tests/src/.../6.1.0.Final` project, no `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/`, no `build/tests/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/`, and the issue metrics worktree only contains the baseline `script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json` and `script_run_metrics/fix_javac_fail.json` files, with no `hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final` run entry. No matching run logs were found.\\n\\nThe repo also shows a likely coordinate-transition problem: `metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/index.json` stops at `6.0.0.Final`, while `metadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/index.json` handles `6.1.x` and uses `6.1.1.Final` as the test version for `6.1.*`. The test directories mirror that split: `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/` exists, `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/6.1.1.Final/` exists, but there is no `6.1.0.Final` project under either path. That makes the `org.hibernate` -> `org.hibernate.orm` handoff the most plausible reason the automation never reached later Gradle/test-generation stages.\\n\\nRelevant paths to inspect:\\n- `logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_818.log`\\n- `metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/index.json`\\n- `metadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/index.json`\\n- `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/`\\n- `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/6.1.1.Final/`\\n\\n1. Verify whether this issue should target `org.hibernate.orm:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final` instead of `org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final`.\\n2. Reproduce locally with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final --stacktrace`; if that fails during setup/lookup, retry with the corrected `org.hibernate.orm` coordinate and capture the first failing Gradle task/output.\\n3. If the coordinate needs to move to `org.hibernate.orm`, seed `6.1.0.Final` from the existing `6.1.1.Final` Hibernate test/metadata layout and rerun the compatibility workflow.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T12:56:26Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/818#issuecomment-4335440550\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDbYhg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-818-fails-java-run-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.1.0.Final-30783e85\\n\\nMost likely failure sequence:\\n- The original `fails-java-run` failure is a real JVM test failure in `OracleDialectHibernateTest`: Hibernate 6.1.0.Final initializes `OracleArrayJdbcType`, which tries to load `oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection`, and the test run fails with `ClassNotFoundException: oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection`. See `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T07-33-56-661220Z.log`.\\n- The preserved work branch contains a candidate fix adding `com.oracle.database.jdbc:ojdbc11:23.2.0.0` to `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.1.0.Final/build.gradle`; the rationale and diff are recorded in `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T07-35-17-139975Z.log`.\\n- After that candidate fix, the workflow appears to get past the original Oracle JDBC classpath problem, but it still fails in the native validation lane: `:nativeTest` reports `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect`, `StrategySelectionException`/`NoSuchMethodException` for `org.hibernate.dialect.SQLServerDialect`, and `OracleDialectHibernateTest` fails with `Could not interpret id generator strategy [org.hibernate.id.enhanced.TableGenerator]`. See `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T07-35-17-147693Z.log` and `build/tests/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/41f4ec5b980eafff5dccd464311141f1.out`.\\n- Native trace verification also surfaces a missing resource registration for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`; see `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T07-36-13-040719Z.log`.\\n- Metrics show the automation did not finish a successful repair/finalization: `stats/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.1.0.Final/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, and the same starting/ending commit `f5339f87a3aa25f82a18de7b92533cd34b063416`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review/cherry-pick the preserved branch change adding `ojdbc11` and rerun the targeted JVM test lane to confirm the original `oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection` failure is resolved.\\n2. Investigate the native regressions separately, especially the inactive H2 reflection metadata condition (`typeReached: org.h2.Driver`), SQLServer dialect instantiation, and the Oracle `TableGenerator` mapping failure.\\n3. If the JVM fix is sufficient for this issue, land that minimal fix first and file a separate follow-up for the native-image metadata/test failures using the logs above.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T07:38:33Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/818#issuecomment-4365670534\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2025-11-26T00:32:58Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc7_VUq2\",\"name\":\"priority\",\"description\":\"This is a priority issue\",\"color\":\"ffffff\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0olA\",\"name\":\"fails-java-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail during java testing\",\"color\":\"8f51c9\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":818,\"title\":\"[Automation] java run fails for org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T07:38:39Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/818\"}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge7/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/forge_metadata.py:2068:        return \"- No matching run logs were found.\"\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
