url\":\"https://github.com/vjovanov\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-04-28T13:14:30Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-04-28T13:14:30Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-d0044eeb\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was after the JVM test repair, during stats/coverage collection for this coordinate. In `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T13-12-31-752286Z.log`, the original `fails-java-run` error is a stale assertion in `Xml_apisTest.versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` (`actual \\\"1.2.01\\\"` vs expected `\\\"1.0\\\"` at `Xml_apisTest.java:74`), and the same log later shows the test was updated and `./gradlew test` passed with `10 tests successful, 0 failed`. However, the run metrics still report `Generated LOC: 0` and the starting and ending commit both as `ea6ee71c8d9d6d854442ef0d9cad8a0036e43096`, so that validated fix was not recorded. The stronger blocker appears in `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/906df4c8d954eba5a3a9da7b1ae10ee3.out`, where `:jacocoTestReport` fails with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`; this matches `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, which found that Maven Central exposes only the `1.2.01` POM and that it relocates to `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2`. Dynamic-access coverage being unavailable is consistent with that failure.\\n\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T13-12-31-752286Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/0f4a273c0380b8e49ad51ab05a8a08b1.out`, and `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/906df4c8d954eba5a3a9da7b1ae10ee3.out`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Recreate or restore the `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01` test project and reapply the one-line assertion fix so `Version.getVersionNum()` expects `1.2.01`, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`.\\n2. Decide how stats/coverage should handle this relocated, POM-only coordinate: either point the workflow at the actual jar artifact or explicitly treat JaCoCo/dynamic-access coverage as unavailable for this case.\\n3. Rerun the stats/coverage lane after that adjustment and verify whether coverage can be generated or must remain unavailable by design.\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"pin\":null,\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/comments/4335566113/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"event\":\"commented\",\"actor\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\",\"id\":352820,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MjgyMA==\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/352820?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/vjovanov\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/vjovanov\",