ps://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/{archive_format}{/ref}\",\"downloads_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/downloads\",\"issues_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues{/number}\",\"pulls_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pulls{/number}\",\"milestones_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/milestones{/number}\",\"notifications_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/notifications{?since,all,participating}\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/labels{/name}\",\"releases_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/releases{/id}\",\"deployments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/deployments\",\"created_at\":\"2022-06-30T13:29:16Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T17:44:11Z\",\"pushed_at\":\"2026-05-03T17:57:16Z\",\"git_url\":\"git://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata.git\",\"ssh_url\":\"git@github.com:oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata.git\",\"clone_url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata.git\",\"svn_url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata\",\"homepage\":\"\",\"size\":408285,\"stargazers_count\":453,\"watchers_count\":453,\"language\":\"Java\",\"has_issues\":true,\"has_projects\":true,\"has_downloads\":true,\"has_wiki\":false,\"has_pages\":false,\"has_discussions\":false,\"forks_count\":119,\"mirror_url\":null,\"archived\":false,\"disabled\":false,\"open_issues_count\":1580,\"license\":{\"key\":\"cc0-1.0\",\"name\":\"Creative Commons Zero v1.0 Universal\",\"spdx_id\":\"CC0-1.0\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/licenses/cc0-1.0\",\"node_id\":\"MDc6TGljZW5zZTY=\"},\"allow_forking\":true,\"is_template\":false,\"web_commit_signoff_required\":false,\"has_pull_requests\":true,\"pull_request_creation_policy\":\"all\",\"topics\":[],\"visibility\":\"public\",\"forks\":119,\"open_issues\":1580,\"watchers\":453,\"default_branch\":\"master\",\"permissions\":{\"admin\":true,\"maintain\":true,\"push\":true,\"triage\":true,\"pull\":true}},\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pulls/3975\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/3975\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/3975.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/grg.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.0/reachability-metadata.json` is still `{}`, and `stats/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json` remains zeroed (`generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`).\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-56-17-367483Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-56-17-387223Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\n1. Replace the scaffold `IvyTest` and add library-specific tests that actually exercise Ivy’s tracked dynamic-access paths, especially `Configurator`, `IvySettings`, and `Main`.\\n2. Update `metadata/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.0/reachability-metadata.json` based on the exercised paths, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.0`.\\n3. Verify that `tests/src/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` is no longer `0/31` before re-running the automation.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T15:58:49Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2456#issuecomment-4364188536\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:44Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":2456,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T15:58:54Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2456\"},{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBA1ldA\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22` failed. Preserved work is available on this branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2451-library-new-request-org.apache.groovy-groovy-4.0.22-2495617f\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated test validation during native test execution. The post-gen summary shows the generated Groovy suite initially had 8 native-runtime failures; 7 were classified as non-metadata failures caused by Groovy runtime class generation or native-image-incompatible dynamic dispatch (`CallSiteGenerator`, `Tuple$tuple`, `ConfigObject$flatten`, `InvokerHelper$createScript`, `GroovyShell.evaluate`) and were removed, but the remaining test `observableCollectionsPublishMutationEvents()` still fails with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for a proxy implementing `java.beans.PropertyChangeListener`. That exact failure is visible in `build/tests/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/ef80c011666dad0a56325c9c72b66b11.out` and `tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, and is summarized in `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.groovy_groovy_4.0.22.md` and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/metadata-fix/codex.log`. Metrics also ended in failure after 6 iterations in `stats/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/execution-metrics.json`, and no dynamic-access coverage artifact was produced under `tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/build/reports/`.\\n\\nRelevant logs to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-02T04-29-50-896311Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T04-13-08-021405Z.log`\\n- `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.groovy_groovy_4.0.22.md`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/ef80c011666dad0a56325c9c72b66b11.out`\\n\\n1. Add the missing proxy reflection entry for `java.beans.PropertyChangeListener` to `metadata/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/reachability-metadata.json` and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22 --stacktrace`.\\n2. Review whether the removed tests should be rewritten to avoid unsupported Groovy runtime class-definition paths rather than restored as-is.\\n3. If those runtime-generated-code scenarios are intended support targets, decide whether Groovy needs a different strategy than the standard `reachability-metadata.json`-only flow before reopening automation for this library.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:34:56Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2451#issuecomment-4362954100\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:42Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":2451,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:35:03Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2451\"},{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAqCDww\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2` failed. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2448-library-new-request-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2-d1479dd2\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is final test-generation validation, not Gradle/native-image execution. Metrics report `test_generation_failed`, while dynamic-access coverage still reached `16/16 (100.00%)`. The generated suite still contains the scaffold placeholder test at `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/Micrometer_coreTest.java`, and both `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/test-results/test/TEST-io_micrometer.micrometer_core.Micrometer_coreTest.xml` and `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show that this placeholder test actually ran. The generation log `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-58-31-246686Z.log` also shows the scaffold file being read unchanged, while other iterations added class-specific coverage work.\\n\\nPlease inspect these logs first:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-58-31-246686Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-45-13-777820Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T21-00-40-685006Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Remove or replace `Micrometer_coreTest.java` with a real Micrometer-specific test so no scaffold placeholder remains in the suite.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2` from the preserved branch.\\n3. If those pass cleanly, keep the generated Micrometer-specific tests and continue the normal `library-new-request` flow from the preserved branch.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T21:03:08Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2448#issuecomment-4339041219\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBAwhdw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`. Preserved work is available on the preserved branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2448-library-new-request-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2-796139b0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test validation during the final test-generation/refinement loop. The preserved branch does contain generated tests, but `build/tests/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/ce959c4146d61e859d232d1fe4339e3d.out` shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED` with 4 failing tests:\\n- `HazelcastIMapAdapterTest.bindsLegacyHazelcastIMapThroughIsolatedPublicCacheBinder()` -> `Expecting not blank but was: null`\\n- `ProcessorMetricsTest.bindsProcessorGaugesAndReadsCpuUsageValues()` -> `Expecting NaN to be finite`\\n- `PropertyValidatorTest.simpleConfigModeResolvesEnumValueIgnoringCase()` -> `NoSuchMethodException: io.micrometer.core.instrument.simple.CountingMode.values()`\\n- `PropertyValidatorTest.getEnumReportsMalformedValueWithAllowedEnumConstants()` -> the same `NoSuchMethodException`\\n\\nThere is also scaffold left behind: the same native test output still prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`, and `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/Micrometer_coreTest.java` is still the placeholder scaffold. Dynamic-access coverage improved to `15/16` (`93.75%`), but `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows one uncovered call site: `io.micrometer.core.instrument.binder.cache.HazelcastIMapAdapter.resolveOneOf(HazelcastIMapAdapter.java:222)`. The final generation logs also show source-context path errors (`ENOENT`) while reading Micrometer sources, which may have interrupted the last refinement pass.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-57-58-812901Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-51-49-607788Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/ce959c4146d61e859d232d1fe4339e3d.out`\\n- `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace/remove the scaffold placeholder in `Micrometer_coreTest` and keep the suite library-specific.\\n2. Fix the 4 native-image test failures above and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`.\\n3. Add or refine coverage for `HazelcastIMapAdapter.resolveOneOf(HazelcastIMapAdapter.java:222)`, then rerun `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:01:42Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2448#issuecomment-4362871159\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:33Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":2448,\"title\":\"Support for io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:01:49Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2448\"},{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAfJTwg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2442-library-new-request-cglib-cglib-nodep-2.2.2-f959b570\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was iterative test-generation validation, not artifact discovery. The run metrics ended in failure after 25 iterations with no surviving output (`generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, `artifacts.metadata_file: None`) in `local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2442-37f7901e/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json`, even though the dynamic-access report reached 44/62 call sites (70.97%).\\n\\nThe preserved Gradle outputs show two concrete blockers. First, `build/tests/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/c3113270d1f69940678f33f6a5acf714.out` shows `:nativeTest` failing with 28 test failures; the dominant root cause is `net.sf.cglib.core.ReflectUtils` failing during native execution because `java.lang.ClassLoader.defineClass(String, byte[], int, int, ProtectionDomain)` is not found (`NoSuchMethodException` / `CodeGenerationException`), with follow-on failures including `ClassNotFoundException: net.sf.cglib.transform.AbstractClassTransformer` and an `IllegalArgumentException` around `UndeclaredThrowableException`. Second, `build/tests/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/561169cc4cebcc950bde480b0c3a0e5e.out` shows a later retry failing `:jacocoTestReport` because the generated `build.gradle` tries to parse `jacocoTestReport.xml`, but the XML contains a DOCTYPE and the parser rejects it (`DOCTYPE is disallowed ...`, build file line 33).\\n\\nLogs worth inspecting:\\n- `logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T13-57-54-715617Z.log`\\n- `logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T13-23-54-287397Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/c3113270d1f69940678f33f6a5acf714.out`\\n- `build/tests/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/561169cc4cebcc950bde480b0c3a0e5e.out`\\n\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and decide whether to salvage the partial cglib-specific tests/metadata from the logged attempts or restart from the scaffold.\\n2. Rework the test set around cglib behavior that can run under native image without depending on `ReflectUtils` / `ClassLoader.defineClass(...)`, or add the missing metadata/configuration if that reflective path must be exercised.\\n3. Remove or replace the custom JaCoCo XML post-processing, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T14:06:19Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2442#issuecomment-4327625666\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBBUVwA\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2442-library-new-request-cglib-cglib-nodep-2.2.2-f860ecc9\\n\\nThis appears to be a post-generation test-validation failure, not a metadata-coverage failure. `stats/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/execution-metrics.json` shows `add_new_library_support` finished successfully with `62/62` dynamic-access coverage, and `human-intervention-logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-02T08-57-16-708576Z.log` shows the follow-up checkstyle issue was auto-fixed. The strongest evidence is in `human-intervention-logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/metadata-fix/codex.log`: it explicitly says the failure was not a metadata gap, but that `tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/CoreMethodWrapperTest.java` assumed a null-parent `URLClassLoader` could reload `net.sf.cglib.core.MethodWrapper` under Native Image, which surfaced as a native-only `ClassNotFoundException`. That same log records that after adjusting this test behavior, `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2` passed.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-02T08-57-16-708576Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T08-42-06-887276Z.log`\\n- `stats/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially `CoreMethodWrapperTest.java`, and confirm the native-only dynamic-loading fallback is acceptable for this new-library test.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2` on the preserved branch, ideally with `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all`.\\n3. If that behavior is acceptable, open or update the PR from the preserved branch; otherwise replace or simplify the failing `CoreMethodWrapperTest` coverage path.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T08:59:48Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2442#issuecomment-4363457984\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:19Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"}],\"number\":2442,\"title\":\"Support for cglib:cglib-nodep:2.2.2\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T07:23:05Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2442\"}]\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/4834.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MjcwMzI1\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"graalvmbot\",\"name\":\"graalvm bot\"},\"body\":\"## native-image run on ubuntu-latest / JDK 25 / mode current-defaults\\n\\nFailure kind: native-image run\\nOS: ubuntu-latest\\nJDK: 25\\nNative-image mode: current-defaults\\nReproducer: `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\"current-defaults\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"4.1.79.F