n-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`, the reproduced failure is `Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Can't find '[toLeakAwareBuffer]' in io.netty.buffer.AbstractByteBufAllocator`, followed by `Test for io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final failed with exit code 1`. The preserved branch adds `metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json` with the two `AbstractByteBufAllocator.toLeakAwareBuffer(...)` overloads, and the same log later shows `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `Test for io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final passed.` `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` looks healthy, and `stats/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/stats.json` reports `coveredCalls: 0` and `totalCalls: 0`, so dynamic-access coverage is not useful here.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json`\\n- `stats/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/stats.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch diff and confirm the added `AbstractByteBufAllocator.toLeakAwareBuffer(...)` reflection entry is acceptable for `netty-codec-xml`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final --stacktrace` from the preserved branch or on a clean branch with the same metadata change.\\n3. If the rerun is green, open a PR with the preserved fix; if CI still fails, compare the rerun output with the preserved `metadata-fix` log for environment-specific differences.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T13:49:04Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metada