n> Get more help at https://help.gradle.org.\\n\\nDeprecated Gradle features were used in this build, making it incompatible with Gradle 10.\\n\\nYou can use '--warning-mode all' to show the individual deprecation warnings and determine if they come from your own scripts or plugins.\\n\\nFor more on this, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\n\\nBUILD FAILED in 2s\\n11 actionable tasks: 3 executed, 8 up-to-date\\n❌ ERROR: 'javac compile' for 1.11.0 failed with exit code 1.\\nFAILED[javac compile][1.11.0][GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\"future-defaults-all\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"1.11.0\\\" ./gradlew clean compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=\\\"org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.10.4\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBD6N9A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5185-fails-javac-compile-org.junit.platform-junit-platform-engine-1.11.0-6d904d94\\n\\nThe original failing stage was `:compileTestJava`: `human-intervention-logs/org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T12-27-08-337119Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-26-34-170073Z.log` both show `ForkJoinPoolHierarchicalTestExecutorServiceTest.java` failing at lines 106 and 111 with `method does not override or implement a method from a supertype`, which points to the generated `NoOpResourceLock` implementation no longer matching the `1.11.0` `ResourceLock` API.\\n\\nHowever, the most likely stage that actually failed this run was post-fix persistence/reporting, not Gradle verification. Three later reruns (`human-intervention-logs/org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-27-08-340112Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-29-16-196102Z.log`, and `.../gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-29-40-032127Z.log`) all end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `Test for org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0 passed`, including a successful native test run. Despite that, `stats/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-engine/1.11.0/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and `starting_commit == ending_commit == 060e7408bf2d6b0faa67782df195de3f0f9c6f42`; the preserved commit on this branch also deleted `tests/src/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-engine/1.11.0/*`, so the successful local fix was not preserved.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T12-27-08-337119Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-26-34-170073Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-29-40-032127Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-engine/1.11.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Recreate or recover the successful `tests/src/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-engine/1.11.0` changes on top of `060e7408bf2d6b0faa67782df195de3f0f9c6f42`, most likely by adapting/removing the stale `ResourceLock` override methods in `ForkJoinPoolHierarchicalTestExecutorServiceTest`.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0` to confirm both compile and native lanes still pass.\\n3. Commit the regenerated test tree (and any required index updates), since the current preserved branch only contains logs plus `stats/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-engine/1.11.0/execution-metrics.json`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T12:32:12Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/5185#issuecomment-4366175732\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T12:13:12Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0jNw\",\"name\":\"fails-javac-compile\",\"description\":\"Tests fail in `javac` compilation\",\"color\":\"a260ed\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":5185,\"title\":\"[Automation] javac compile fails for org.junit.platform:junit-platform-engine:1.11.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T12:32:18Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/5185\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/2858.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njavassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAqPrzg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` failed during test generation/review, even though the workflow completed and metrics were produced. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2858-library-new-request-javassist-javassist-3.12.0.GA-d4ec2b2d\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is `add-new-library-support`, not Gradle validation. In `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-56-58-918845Z.log`, the generator adds `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/RuntimeSupportInnerDefaultMethodHandlerTest.java` specifically to cover `javassist.util.proxy.RuntimeSupport$DefaultMethodHandler.invoke()` / `Method#invoke(...)`, but the preserved test now disables itself under native image via `assumeFalse(NativeImageConditions.isNativeImageRuntime())`. The preserved branch also adds `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/NativeImageConditions.java`, and there are 8 native-image skip sites across the generated tests, so the suite is not acceptable native-image coverage for a new-library request. Metrics still show `93/105` dynamic-access coverage (`88.57%`) in `stats/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/stats.json`, which suggests the blocker is test quality rather than missing metadata generation. For reference, `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-28T21-22-53-179914Z.log` reports `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, so style was not the failure.\\n\\nRelevant paths to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-56-58-918845Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T21-00-10-395357Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-28T21-22-53-179914Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/RuntimeSupportInnerDefaultMethodHandlerTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/NativeImageConditions.java`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Remove or rewrite the generated tests that call `NativeImageConditions.isNativeImageRuntime()`, especially `RuntimeSupportInnerDefaultMethodHandlerTest`, so the targeted behavior actually runs under native image.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA`.\\n3. If the preserved branch still looks useful after that cleanup, continue from it and open a manual PR.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T21:36:57Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2858#issuecomment-4339264462\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA_y-jQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2858-library-new-request-javassist-javassist-3.12.0.GA-4653b8b0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation / validation rather than coverage collection. Metrics still ended in `failure` after 43 iterations and 2410 generated LOC, even though dynamic-access coverage reached `102/105 (97.14%)`. The generation logs show multiple unresolved generated-test problems: `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-11-31-685957Z.log` has `:compileTestJava FAILED` in `FactoryHelperTest` (`String cannot be converted to CtClass`), `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-55-44-991233Z.log` has `SecurityActionsTest` failing with `javassist.CannotCompileException: no such class: javassist.util.proxy.SecurityActions`, and earlier generation logs include native missing-registration failures. The last preserved generation attempt, `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-32-34-992805Z.log`, only adds `SecurityActionsAnonymous6Test` and explicitly says tests were not run, so the job never reached a final green verification pass.\\n\\nThe preserved follow-up in `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/metadata-fix/codex.log` is the best hint for manual recovery: it reproduces the remaining native issue under `future-defaults-all`, shows repeated `ServiceConfigurationError` lines for JDI connectors, then updates metadata for the `Viewer` resource and JDI connector reflection and adjusts `HotSwapperTest` for native `no Connectors loaded`; that reproducer finishes with `42 tests successful, 0 failed`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and compare it against `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/metadata-fix/codex.log`, especially the `HotSwapperTest` and `SecurityActions*` changes.\\n2. Re-run `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` and confirm the JDI connector path is handled correctly.\\n3. If that passes, clean up the final diff and resume the issue with the preserved branch as the starting point.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:06:27Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2858#issuecomment-4361862797\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEejZw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` with workflow status `failure`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2858-library-new-request-javassist-javassist-3.12.0.GA-0ba22118\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation, or an earlier setup step immediately before generated tests/metadata were written. Evidence: the preserved branch does not contain any diff for this issue, there is no generated `metadata/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/` tree, there is no generated `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/` tree, and both `forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2858-6806a602/forge/script_run_metrics/` and `forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2858-6806a602/forge/benchmark_run_metrics/` are empty. No run-specific `add-new-library-support`, Gradle, or metrics logs were preserved for this coordinate under `forge/logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/`; the only available file there is `forge/logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_2858.log`, which is the later human-follow-up analysis log rather than the original failing run.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `forge/logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_2858.log`\\n- `forge/logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/`\\n- `forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2858-6806a602/forge/script_run_metrics/`\\n- `forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2858-6806a602/forge/benchmark_run_metrics/`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Re-run the `library-new-request` workflow for `javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` and capture the first `add-new-library-support` / Gradle log that fails.\\n2. Check why this run did not persist generation logs or pending metrics for issue `2858`.\\n3. Continue from the preserved branch only after confirming whether generation failed before any `javassist` test or metadata files were created.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T17:41:34Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2858#issuecomment-4366771047\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:30Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\