ated, `metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.2.2.Final/` is empty, and there is no `stats/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.2.2.Final/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `/home/vjovanov/.gradle/daemon/9.1.0/daemon-3742815.out.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/.gradle/daemon/9.1.0/daemon-3744276.out.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5203-5ca02869/tests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.1.74.Final/build/test-results/test/TEST-Gradle#20Test#20Run#20#3atest.xml`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5203-5ca02869/build/reports/problems/problems-report.html`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5203-5ca02869/tests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.1.74.Final/build/reports/problems/problems-report.html`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Re-run the `fixTestNativeImageRun` flow in an environment where the GraalVM `native-image-agent` shared library is installed and visible on the test JVM library path.\\n2. Confirm that the rerun actually creates `tests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.2.2.Final` and `metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.2.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json` before investigating any library-specific native-image regression.\\n3. If it still fails after the agent-library issue is fixed, capture the new workflow/native-image logs and the `stats/io.netty/netty-codec-smtp/4.2.2.Final` outputs for follow-up.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T15:57:40Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/5203#issuecomment-4366570182\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T13:37:13Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0ftA\",\"name\":\"fails-native-image-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail in native execution\",\"color\":\"d93f0b\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":5203,\"title\":\"[Automation] native-image run fails for io.netty:netty-codec-smtp:4.2.2.Final\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T15:57:46Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/5203\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/2861.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njavax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBAX-Mg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2861-library-new-request-javax.servlet-jsp-api-2.0-8b9306c8\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation / dynamic-access coverage improvement, not basic test execution. The preserved run added `SimpleTagSupportTest` and `TagSupportTest`, and the JVM/native test result XML under `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/test-results/` shows those tests passed, but `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still reports `0/2` covered calls for `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)`. The run metrics also ended in failure with `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `test_file` / `metadata_file` still `None` in `stats/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/execution-metrics.json`, which matches the `test_generation_failed` workflow status.\\n\\nThere is also an upstream-context gap that likely hurt generation: both generation logs say the main sources were unavailable (`URL: N/A` / `no URL in index.json`), and artifact discovery left `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, and `test-code-url` as `N/A` for this coordinate. Please inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-43-25-132367Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-52-14-878334Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved tests on the branch, especially `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java` and `TagSupportTest.java`, and decide whether the synthetic `class$` call sites are realistically coverable for this library.\\n2. Fill in any recoverable upstream metadata for `metadata/javax.servlet/jsp-api/index.json` so future runs are not operating with `source-code-url` / `repository-url` / `test-code-url` set to `N/A`.\\n3. Either replace the current tests with a library-specific approach that actually exercises those two `Class.forName` paths, or document that these call sites are not practically coverable and handle the coordinate manually.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:00:35Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2861#issuecomment-4362468914\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEeLag\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2861-library-new-request-javax.servlet-jsp-api-2.0-cf1ed261\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is test generation / dynamic-access coverage, with a separate final validation rerun failure in the environment. The preserved branch adds `TagSupportTest` and `SimpleTagSupportTest`, but the scaffold `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/Jsp_apiTest.java` is still unchanged and prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`. That placeholder is what executes in the successful native test runs recorded in `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-27-04-240996Z.log`, `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-30-18-829891Z.log`, and `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-34-17-358618Z.log`. The generated dynamic-access report at `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows `0/2` covered calls, with both `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)` still uncovered. On top of that, the final rerun in `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-36-13-307892Z.log` and `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-36-39-549640Z.log` aborts immediately because `JAVA_HOME` points to an invalid directory. The metrics file `stats/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/execution-metrics.json` also records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file/metadata_file: None`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T17-27-04-220726Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T17-36-13-288873Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-27-04-240996Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-30-18-829891Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-34-17-358618Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T17-36-13-307892Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the scaffold `Jsp_apiTest` with library-specific tests that actually execute the `TagSupport.class$` and `SimpleTagSupport.class$` paths, then rerun coverage for `javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0`.\\n2. Recheck `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` and confirm coverage improves from `0/2`.\\n3. Fix the `JAVA_HOME` / GraalVM environment used by the final validation rerun and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0`.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T17:38:12Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2861#issuecomment-4366764906\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:31Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":2861,\"title\":\"Support for javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T17:38:17Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2861\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/4516.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nsoftware.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBD44RA\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4516-library-new-request-software.amazon.awssdk-third-party-jackson-core-2.34.0-e368f361\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / test-generation persistence, not downstream validation. `stats/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the same starting/ending commit (`6c4a09d65c5d043047a65661b567e5bd2d719137`). At the same time, `logs/software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T12-16-29-434541Z.log` shows the generator claiming it replaced the scaffold with `VersionUtilTest`, added a `pom.properties` fixture, and added test-only reachability metadata. The downstream logs then show those generated tests running successfully: `logs/software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T12-16-29-452615Z.log` reports both `VersionUtilTest` methods as `SUCCESSFUL`, and `logs/software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T12-18-00-639259Z.log` ends `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`. The dynamic-access report under `tests/src/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows 4/4 covered calls.\\n\\nThe source/build state is inconsistent: `tests/src/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/src/test/java/software_amazon_awssdk/third_party_jackson_core/Third_party_jackson_coreTest.java` is still the untouched placeholder, while the generated fixture files exist only under `tests/src/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/build/resources/test/...`. That strongly suggests the generated test/resources were produced during the run but never persisted into the source tree.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Recover or recreate `VersionUtilTest`, `src/test/resources/META-INF/maven/com/example/versionutil/versionutil-fixture/pom.properties`, and `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json` from the generation log and build outputs on the preserved branch.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0` to confirm the recovered sources still pass and keep 4/4 dynamic-access coverage.\\n3. Commit the recovered test/resources to the preserved branch and continue the issue from there.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T12:20:14Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4516#issuecomment-4366153796\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T06:21:00Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":4516,\"title\":\"Support for software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T12:20:19Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4516\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/3276.json:1:{\"assignees\":[{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MjgyMA==\",\"login\":\"vjovanov\",\"name\":\"Vojin Jovanovic\"}],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA-kXwQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3276-library-new-request-com.sun.xml.dtd-parser-dtd-parser-1.5.1-c5f569bb\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation `nativeTest` run. The generated work did improve dynamic-access coverage to `8/9`, but `build/tests/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/3707db0411d0e6d6eff1f2a466a012f0.out` ends with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTest'` and 9 native test failures. `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows repeated `MissingResourceException` for `com_sun_xml_dtd_parser.dtd_parser.resources.Messages` and `ResolverTest` errors for `/unreachable-widget.dtd (No such file or directory)`, so the generated resource-loading tests are not working under Native Image. The generated suite is also incomplete: `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/src/test/java/com_sun_xml_dtd_parser/dtd_parser/Dtd_parserTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, and `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still leaves `MessageCatalog.isLocaleSupported(MessageCatalog.java:506)` via `ClassLoader#getSystemResourceAsStream(...)` uncovered.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-56-45-615754Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-08-27-828177Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/3707db0411d0e6d6eff1f2a466a012f0.out`\\n- `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Replace the remaining scaffold placeholder test with a library-specific test or remove it if it is unnecessary.\\n- Fix the generated `MessageCatalog`/`Resolver` tests so their bundles and DTD resources are available under Native Image, then rerun the native tests.\\n- Add one focused test for the remaining uncovered `MessageCatalog.isLocaleSupported()` system-resource path and refresh the dynamic-access coverage report.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:11:21Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3276#issuecomment-4360574913\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBER1-w\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3276-library-new-request-com.sun.xml.dtd-parser-dtd-parser-1.5.1-798e5822\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation followed by native-trace verification. `stats/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no generated test or metadata artifact was recorded. The current source tree still only has the scaffold `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/src/test/java/com_sun_xml_dtd_parser/dtd_parser/Dtd_parserTest.java`. At the same time, `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` stayed at 5/9 coverage, with both `Resolver` call sites still uncovered and `MessageCatalog.isLocaleSupported(...)` still missing the `Class.forName(...)` and `ClassLoader#getSystemResourceAsStream(...)` paths.\\n\\nThe native-trace logs show repeated missing-registration/resource failures rather than a converging fix:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/native-test-verify/cycle-5-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-42-24-370128Z.log`: missing resource registration for `com_sun_xml_dtd_parser/dtd_parser/resources/Messages_en.properties`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/native-test-verify/cycle-6-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-43-42-348667Z.log`: missing reflection registration for `com_sun_xml_dtd_parser.dtd_parser.resources.Messages_es_MX`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/native-test-verify/cycle-10-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-48-20-828430Z.log`: missing resource bundle registration for `com_sun_xml_dtd_parser.dtd_parser.resources.Messages`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/native-test-verify/cycle-11-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-49-25-893882Z.log` and `.../cycle-12-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-50-40-476762Z.log`: missing reflection/constructor registration for `sun.text.resources.cldr.ext.FormatData_de`\\n\\nAlso inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T15-34-31-997931Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T15-34-32-037940Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Replace the placeholder test with real library-specific tests for `MessageCatalog` and `Resolver`, and make sure the source files are actually present under `tests/src/...` before rerunning.\\n- Re-run native trace/native test and fix the missing resource/reflection registrations shown above, especially the `Messages*` bundles and the locale-data access triggered by `MessageFormat`.\\n- Refresh dynamic-access coverage and confirm the remaining uncovered call sites (`Resolver` 0/2 and the two `MessageCatalog.isLocaleSupported(...)` paths) are exercised.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T15:53:42Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3276#issuecomment-4366562811\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T06:43:51Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc7_VUq2\",\"name\":\"priority\",\"description\":\"This is a priority issue\",\"color\":\"ffffff\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":3276,\"title\":\"Support for com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T15:55:14Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3276\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/2894.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncommons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA-0AwQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2894-library-new-request-commons-beanutils-commons-beanutils-core-1.8.0-1c4ec19a`\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: the dynamic-access test-generation loop did not actually cover the remaining `LocaleConvertUtilsBean` sites. In `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-02-59-740412Z.log`, the final attempt targets `org.apache.commons.beanutils.locale.LocaleConvertUtilsBean` and claims it added `LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.java` to hit `Class#forName` and `Array#newInstance`, but `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows `LocaleConvertUtilsBean` at `0/2` covered and overall dynamic-access coverage remains `69/94 (73.40%)`. The run metrics in `stats/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/execution-metrics.json` also stayed on the starting commit (`da97572125ad0572ccf9e5904a3e516bf740dea5` -> same commit) and recorded `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, which matches the `test_generation_failed` reason.\\n\\nThere is also preserved but incomplete follow-up work: the branch adds `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.java`, and its JVM report passes in `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-commons_beanutils.commons_beanutils_core.LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.xml`, but the metadata file is still `{}` and native execution still has 16 errors in `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`. An earlier attempt worth checking is `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-55-15-161610Z.log`, which worked on `WrapDynaClassTest` but that source file was not preserved in the final commit.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved `LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.java` and the earlier `WrapDynaClassTest` attempt from the logs, then replace/refine the generated test so it actually hits the two uncovered `LocaleConvertUtilsBean` dynamic-access call sites.\\n2. Add the missing reachability metadata needed for the native failures instead of leaving `metadata/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/reachability-metadata.json` empty.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0` and confirm both the dynamic-access report improves past `69/94` and the native errors are gone.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:06:39Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2894#issuecomment-4360831169\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEW3bg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2894-library-new-request-commons-beanutils-commons-beanutils-core-1.8.0-6435ea8b\\n\\nThe most likely blocking stage was native trace verification after transient test generation, followed by the generated work not being preserved. `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T16-28-39-734940Z.log` shows a generated `MethodUtilsTest` with 8 passing tests and a successful `nativeTest`, but all native trace verification cycles then stop with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Thread#getContextClassLoader()` / reflective invocation from `org.apache.commons.logging.LogFactory`, reached from `org.apache.commons.beanutils.MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod()` and `MethodUtils.invokeMethod()` in `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T16-31-12-302922Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/native-test-verify/cycle-1-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T16-32-06-877884Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/native-test-verify/cycle-2-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T16-32-59-831443Z.log`. The collected trace metadata under `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/natively-collected/runs/cycle-{0,1,2}/reachability-metadata.json` points at `org.apache.commons.logging.LogFactory`, and `stats/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/execution-metrics.json` shows the run ended with no preserved output (`generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, unchanged start/end commit). The preserved branch currently contains only the placeholder scaffold test and `{}` metadata, and the reported dynamic-access coverage is still only 10/94 (10.64%).\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Recover or recreate the transient `MethodUtilsTest` from the build artifacts (`tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-commons_beanutils.commons_beanutils_core.MethodUtilsTest.xml` and compiled classes under `build/classes/java/test`) and commit it on the preserved branch.\\n2. Add or adjust metadata for the downstream `commons-logging` path exercised by `MethodUtils` (`LogFactory` / `Thread.getContextClassLoader`) so native trace verification can complete.\\n3. Re-run the library test and dynamic-access verification for `commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0` and confirm coverage improves materially from 10/94.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T16:35:40Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2894#issuecomment-4366645102\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:50Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":2894,\"title\":\"Support for commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T16:35:45Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2894\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/4478.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MjgyMA==\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"vjovanov\",\"name\":\"Vojin Jovanovic\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEXq0A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4478-library-new-request-com.google.cloud-google-cloud-spanner-6.116.1-554ea80f\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: test generation/preservation. In `logs/com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T16-34-37-052054Z.log`, the generator claims it added `ClientSideStatementSetExecutorTest.java`, but `stats/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-spanner/6.116.1/execution-metrics.json` reports `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the run started and ended on the same commit (`b25b2a0f077f21f64f2c3424cb8696059336a629`). In the preserved worktree, `tests/src/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-spanner/6.116.1/src/test/java` only contains the scaffold `Google_cloud_spannerTest.java`, and `tests/src/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-spanner/6.116.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-com_google_cloud.google_cloud_spanner.Google_cloud_spannerTest.xml` shows it only printed `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`.\\n\\nThere is also evidence that a useful test existed transiently during the run: `tests/src/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-spanner/6.116.1/build/classes/java/test/com_google_cloud/google_cloud_spanner/ClientSideStatementSetExecutorTest.class` and `tests/src/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-spanner/6.116.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-com_google_cloud.google_cloud_spanner.ClientSideStatementSetExecutorTest.xml` show a passing test that exercised `set autocommit = false` and `set retry_aborts_internally = false`. Dynamic-access coverage ended at 22/43 (51.16%). For additional context, inspect `logs/com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T16-34-37-299794Z.log` (placeholder test output and `UNAUTHENTICATED` Spanner call) and `logs/com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T16-38-35-450888Z.log` (`MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `io.grpc.netty.shaded.io.netty.channel.unix.DatagramSocketAddress`).\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Recover or recreate `ClientSideStatementSetExecutorTest.java` from the transient build outputs and add it under `tests/src/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-spanner/6.116.1/src/test/java/...`.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1` and `./gradlew nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1` to confirm the test is preserved and the 22/43 coverage is reproducible from source.\\n3. If native trace still reports the Netty `DatagramSocketAddress` reflection error, investigate whether additional metadata is needed beyond the recovered test.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T16:43:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4478#issuecomment-4366658256\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T06:19:56Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":4478,\"title\":\"Support for com.google.cloud:google-cloud-spanner:6.116.1\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T16:43:12Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4478\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/2574.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MjcwMzI1\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"graalvmbot\",\"name\":\"graalvm bot\"},\"body\":\"## java run on ubuntu-latest / JDK 25 / mode current-defaults\\n\\nFailure kind: java run\\nOS: ubuntu-latest\\nJDK: 25\\nNative-image mode: current-defaults\\nReproducer: `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\"current-defaults\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"1.2.01\\\" ./gradlew clean javaTest -Pcoordinates=\\\"xml-apis:xml-apis:1.0.b2\\\"`\\nRunner log: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/actions/runs/25027281349/job/73301240502\\nLast 300 lines of the log:\\n```console\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:pluginDescriptors UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:processResources UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:classes UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :tck-build-logic:jar UP-TO-DATE\\n> Task :clean UP-TO-DATE\\n\\n[Incubating] Problems report is available at: file:///home/runner/work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.0.b