D[native-image run][4.1.79.Final][GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\"future-defaults-all\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\"4.1.79.Final\\\" ./gradlew clean test -Pcoordinates=\\\"io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.74.Final\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBBJyFg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4175-fails-native-image-run-io.netty-netty-transport-sctp-4.1.79.Final-8f6ebdf3\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `nativeTestCompile`, not artifact URL population. `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` ends successfully, while `build/tests/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/3362232c88035a1917202ce564dba0b5.out` shows `Execution failed for task ':nativeTestCompile'` and a native-image linker failure with undefined references to multiple `Java_sun_nio_ch_sctp_SctpNet_*` symbols. The detailed linker report is in `tests/src/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.74.Final/build/native/nativeTestCompile/svm_err_b_20260502T092403.655_pid717536.md`.\\n\\nThere is also likely salvageable work: `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log` ends with a successful local rerun of `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final --stacktrace` after adding reflection metadata for `io.netty.buffer.AbstractByteBufAllocator.toLeakAwareBuffer(...)` guarded by `io.netty.buffer.ByteBufUtil`. Dynamic-access coverage and run metrics were unavailable for the failed automation run.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Inspect `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log` and recover the recorded metadata change for `metadata/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json` (and the related `index.json` entry if needed).\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final --stacktrace`; if it still fails, focus on the SCTP linker errors in `build/tests/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/3362232c88035a1917202ce564dba0b5.out` and the `svm_err_*.md` report.\\n3. If the metadata recovery passes locally, open a PR from the recovered change set; otherwise escalate as a GraalVM/JDK SCTP toolchain issue with the linker logs attached.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T07:26:05Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4175#issuecomment-4363285014\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBB-Vhw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4175-fails-native-image-run-io.netty-netty-transport-sctp-4.1.79.Final-ff31db9e\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `nativeTestCompile`. In `build/tests/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/8707d0739144a2a9468b765c1db6006f.out`, the native-image link step fails with undefined SCTP JNI symbols such as `Java_sun_nio_ch_sctp_SctpNet_connect0`, `Java_sun_nio_ch_sctp_SctpNet_socket0`, and `Java_sun_nio_ch_sctp_SctpNet_listen0`, and Gradle ends with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTestCompile'` / `BUILD FAILED in 15s`. The preserved logs also show a later follow-up run that passed after adding metadata (`human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log` and `build/tests/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/98a503bf6792fc4174432a8ef2a0abed.out`), so this looks more like an environment/toolchain-specific SCTP native-image problem than a clean missing-metadata-only failure.\\n\\nThe URL population step completed successfully (`human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`). Metrics are limited: `stats/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.79.Final/stats.json` reports `dynamicAccess: \\\"N/A\\\"` and only library coverage data.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated `metadata/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json` and `metadata/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/index.json` changes.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final --stacktrace` in a CI-like environment to confirm whether `nativeTestCompile` still fails with the `Java_sun_nio_ch_sctp_SctpNet_*` linker errors.\\n3. If the linker failure reproduces, treat this as an SCTP/JDK/GraalVM native-image environment issue and decide whether the SCTP native test needs an environment-specific adjustment or should be skipped/not supported for native-image.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T15:34:31Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4175#issuecomment-4364146055\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDgfiw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4175-fails-native-image-run-io.netty-netty-transport-sctp-4.1.79.Final-c27a162d\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is `nativeTestCompile` / native-image link for the existing `tests/src/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.74.Final` test project, not JVM test execution. The JVM tests passed, but the preserved native-image error report shows the linker failing with unresolved SCTP JNI symbols such as `Java_sun_nio_ch_sctp_SctpNet_socket0`, `...connect0`, `...bindx`, and related `SctpNet_*` entries (`tests/src/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.74.Final/build/native/nativeTestCompile/svm_err_b_20260503T102756.130_pid74495.md`). That points to an environment/platform issue around SCTP native support in the JDK/native-image toolchain rather than missing reachability metadata for `netty-transport-sctp`.\\n\\nThe preserved automation logs are also worth reviewing because the follow-up repair attempt appears to have drifted into shared Netty metadata instead of this library: `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows a later successful rerun that exercised `io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final` and added metadata under `metadata/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json`, while `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` only populated URL metadata for `netty-transport-sctp`. Metrics are limited; `stats/io.netty/netty-transport-sctp/4.1.79.Final/stats.json` reports `dynamicAccess: \\\"N/A\\\"`.\\n\\nSuggested next steps:\\n1. Reproduce `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final` on a machine/toolchain with confirmed SCTP native support, and verify whether the linker failure is specific to the current GraalVM/JDK 25.1.0-dev environment.\\n2. Decide whether SCTP-based native-image tests should be skipped/guarded on unsupported environments, or whether additional native libraries / JDK SCTP support are required in CI.\\n3. Review whether the preserved `netty-common` metadata change is actually relevant to this issue before carrying any part of the preserved branch forward.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T08:29:43Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4175#issuecomment-4365754251\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:06:54Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0ftA\",\"name\":\"fails-native-image-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail in native execution\",\"color\":\"d93f0b\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":4175,\"title\":\"[Automation] native-image run fails for io.netty:netty-transport-sctp:4.1.79.Final\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T08:29:48Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4175\"}\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/3029.json:1:{\"assignees\":[],\"author\":{\"is_bot\":true,\"login\":\"app/github-actions\"},\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBC2F6Q\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3029-library-new-request-org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty-hadoop-shaded-guava-1.1.1-01ba0f77\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / test generation, not Gradle or native-image compilation. In `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T00-43-51-071712Z.log`, the generator claims it added `SerializationTest.java` and test reachability metadata for `org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty.com.google.common.collect.Serialization`, but `stats/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/execution-metrics.json` records `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the starting and ending commit are both `dc717d71825deb94a5a20b904990b2ffee898997`. The current generated tree still contains only the scaffold placeholder test at `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty/hadoop_shaded_guava/Hadoop_shaded_guavaTest.java`, and the preserved branch only adds `metadata/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/reachability-metadata.json` with `{}`.\\n\\nFor comparison, `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T00-43-51-093395Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T00-44-31-672026Z.log` show the scaffold test project compiling and native-image building successfully, which supports the `test_generation_failed` diagnosis rather than an infra failure. Dynamic-access coverage also remains low at 14/121 (11.57%), so the intended `Serialization` coverage work never landed.\\n\\nRecommended manual next steps:\\n1. Reconstruct the missing test changes from the end of `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T00-43-51-071712Z.log`, especially the planned `Serialization` coverage for map, multimap, multiset, and `ConcurrentHashMultiset` paths.\\n2. Add the corresponding non-empty metadata and replace the scaffold placeholder test under `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/`.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1` after the manual changes.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T00:46:13Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3029#issuecomment-4365059561\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDO-WA\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3029-library-new-request-org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty-hadoop-shaded-guava-1.1.1-9fbf2562\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / test-generation persistence. `stats/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the same starting/ending commit (`012b9229f75f6aa91191201576eb4a9dea4dfeb2`). However, `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T05-23-36-154912Z.log` shows the generator claiming it created `SerializationTest` and removed the placeholder test, and `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty.hadoop_shaded_guava.SerializationTest.xml` shows 4 passing tests. In the current worktree, `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty/hadoop_shaded_guava/Hadoop_shaded_guavaTest.java` is still the placeholder and `metadata/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/reachability-metadata.json` is still `{}`, so the generated work was not persisted.\\n\\nThere is also a concrete native-trace blocker. `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T05-24-31-635927Z.log` ends with `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`. The dynamic-access report at `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows only `15/121` covered calls (`12.40%`). That transient `SerializationTest` covered the targeted `Serialization` call sites, but overall coverage is still far below the new-library threshold.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T05-23-36-154912Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T05-24-31-635927Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/execution-metrics.json`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Recover the generated `SerializationTest` from the preserved branch or build outputs and make sure it is actually committed together with any required metadata changes.\\n2. Add the missing test resource registration for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter` so `runNativeTraceImage` can complete.\\n3. Re-run coverage/native verification and expand tests beyond `Serialization` if needed, since `15/121` coverage is still below the acceptance threshold.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T05:26:26Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3029#issuecomment-4365467224\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDyz0A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3029-library-new-request-org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty-hadoop-shaded-guava-1.1.1-201dc3b5\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was automated test generation/preservation. The run metrics ended in `failure` with `generated LOC=0`, `test_file=None`, `metadata_file=None`, and the ending commit unchanged from the starting commit (`a7b9c8f0a208eb819061b3f2522107d67bad6408`). The generation log at `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T11-25-37-437223Z.log` ends with a claim that `SerializationTest.java` was added and the placeholder test was removed, and the JVM test log / JUnit XML (`human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T11-25-37-456343Z.log` and `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty.hadoop_shaded_guava.SerializationTest.xml`) show `SerializationTest` ran successfully. However, the preserved source tree still only contains the scaffold `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty/hadoop_shaded_guava/Hadoop_shaded_guavaTest.java`, and dynamic-access coverage remains only `14/121 (11.57%)` in `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-guava/1.1.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n\\nThere is also a native-trace follow-on problem in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T11-26-42-157433Z.log`: the native test executable throws `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.resources.MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/javax.xml.stream.XMLOutputFactory` while JUnit’s XML report writer initializes.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Recreate and commit the intended serialization-focused test on the preserved branch, replacing the placeholder scaffold with real coverage for the shaded Guava serialization paths.\\n2. Re-run the library tests and dynamic-access report for `org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1`, and confirm coverage reaches at least 50%.\\n3. Fix or work around the native trace resource-registration failure for `META-INF/services/javax.xml.stream.XMLOutputFactory`, then rerun native trace verification.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T11:28:41Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3029#issuecomment-4366054352\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:46Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\",\"name\":\"library-new-request\",\"description\":\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\",\"color\":\"83ff2c\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":3029,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty:hadoop-shaded-guava:1.1.1\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T11:28:47Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3029\"}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
