ommand_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\\\n\\\\nBUILD FAILED in 4s\\\\n11 actionable tasks: 3 executed, 8 up-to-date\\\\n❌ ERROR: 'java run' for 1.2.01 failed with exit code 1.\\\\nFAILED[java run][1.2.01][GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\\\\\"future-defaults-all\\\\\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\" ./gradlew clean javaTest -Pcoordinates=\\\\\\\"xml-apis:xml-apis:1.0.b2\\\\\\\"]\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\",\\\"comments\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAjjYaA\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01` with workflow status `failure`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-8fda82cb\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the initial Java runtime test reproduction/fix stage (`test`/`javaTest`). Concrete evidence: no matching run logs were preserved, run metrics and dynamic-access coverage are unavailable, the preserved branch was created from `HEAD` and pushed with no additional commit, and there is no generated `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/`, `metadata/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/`, or `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/` tree in the preserved worktree. This suggests the job failed before it produced any recoverable `1.2.01` artifacts.\\\\n\\\\nPaths to inspect:\\\\n- `forge_run_metrics/2574-1506b5af/logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/` (expected workflow logs; not present in the scratch metrics repo)\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/` (expected copied logs on the preserved branch; not present)\\\\n- `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/build/test-results/test/` and `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/build/reports/tests/test/` after reproducing locally\\\\n\\\\nNext steps:\\\\n1. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01 --stacktrace` to capture the first runtime failure.\\\\n2. If the `1.2.01` test scaffold is still missing, compare against `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.0.b2/` and decide whether a concrete runtime test needs to be added or adapted before retrying.\\\\n3. Preserve the Gradle output under `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/` or attach it to this issue, then continue the version-bump fix manually.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T03:56:19Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4332247144\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAmt9IQ\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-d0044eeb\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was after the JVM test repair, during stats/coverage collection for this coordinate. In `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T13-12-31-752286Z.log`, the original `fails-java-run` error is a stale assertion in `Xml_apisTest.versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` (`actual \\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\"` vs expected `\\\\\\\"1.0\\\\\\\"` at `Xml_apisTest.java:74`), and the same log later shows the test was updated and `./gradlew test` passed with `10 tests successful, 0 failed`. However, the run metrics still report `Generated LOC: 0` and the starting and ending commit both as `ea6ee71c8d9d6d854442ef0d9cad8a0036e43096`, so that validated fix was not recorded. The stronger blocker appears in `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/906df4c8d954eba5a3a9da7b1ae10ee3.out`, where `:jacocoTestReport` fails with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`; this matches `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, which found that Maven Central exposes only the `1.2.01` POM and that it relocates to `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2`. Dynamic-access coverage being unavailable is consistent with that failure.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T13-12-31-752286Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/0f4a273c0380b8e49ad51ab05a8a08b1.out`, and `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/906df4c8d954eba5a3a9da7b1ae10ee3.out`.\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Recreate or restore the `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01` test project and reapply the one-line assertion fix so `Version.getVersionNum()` expects `1.2.01`, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`.\\\\n2. Decide how stats/coverage should handle this relocated, POM-only coordinate: either point the workflow at the actual jar artifact or explicitly treat JaCoCo/dynamic-access coverage as unavailable for this case.\\\\n3. Rerun the stats/coverage lane after that adjustment and verify whether coverage can be generated or must remain unavailable by design.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T13:14:30Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4335566113\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBCHHbA\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`.\\\\n\\\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-4a91c442\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the `fix-java-run-fail` generation/orchestration step after the original JVM failure was reproduced. The raw Gradle log at `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-42-48-440922Z.log` shows the real failure: `Xml_apisTest > versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` failed because actual `\\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\"` did not contain expected `\\\\\\\"1.0\\\\\\\"` at `Xml_apisTest.java:74`. After that, `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T16-43-43-207622Z.log` shows the automation struggling with source-context resolution (`find: ‘local_repositories/source_context/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/main’: No such file or directory`), and `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, with the same starting and ending commit (`af4b76c33bf1b9d99f5100e78e9751f3911cbe0b`).\\\\n\\\\nLater retries do not show a persistent library/runtime failure: `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-43-43-219421Z.log` and `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-49-43-666186Z.log` both report `versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` and all 10 tests passing. There is also a separate metadata detour in `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/metadata-fix/codex.log`, which does not match the original assertion-based `fails-java-run` problem. Dynamic-access coverage is unavailable for this run.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-42-48-440922Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T16-43-43-207622Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-43-43-219421Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\\\n- `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/execution-metrics.json`\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Recreate the original JVM failure and verify whether `versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` should assert `1.2.01` (or a broader `1.2`-series value) instead of `1.0`.\\\\n2. Ignore the metadata-fix detour unless a clean rerun proves `metadata/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/reachability-metadata.json` is actually required.\\\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01` from a clean worktree, then regenerate stats if needed so the final fix and coverage are captured cleanly.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-02T16:53:30Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4364289900\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDs84w\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job for `xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-7a34b9b0\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the Java test repair step. In `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-22-51-489745Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T10-23-47-354915Z.log`, `Xml_apisTest.versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` fails because `Version.getVersionNum()` returns `\\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\"` but the generated test still asserts that it should contain `\\\\\\\"1.0\\\\\\\"` (`Xml_apisTest.java:74`). The metrics confirm automation never turned that into a usable fix: `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, identical start/end commits, and no recorded test or metadata artifact.\\\\n\\\\nThere was also a secondary failure during trace verification. `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T10-24-17-910503Z.log` aborts with `IllegalArgumentException: Option TraceMetadataConditionPackages must contain package prefixes separated by ','`, which suggests the trace run used `xml-apis` instead of valid Java package prefixes. Later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-23-47-360518Z.log` and `.../gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-29-49-644665Z.log` reached `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, but that success was not captured as a usable automation result.\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Restore or regenerate the `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01` test project and update the version assertion to match `1.2.01` behavior instead of the old `1.0` expectation.\\\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`; if metadata tracing is needed, use valid package prefixes such as `javax.xml,org.apache.xmlcommons,org.w3c.dom,org.xml.sax`.\\\\n3. If the rerun passes, commit the regenerated test/metadata/stats outputs, since the preserved branch only records the failed automation state.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T10:32:43Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4365958371\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true}],\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T01:33:30Z\\\",\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"library-unsupported-version\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"bb366d\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0olA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"fails-java-run\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Tests fail during java testing\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"8f51c9\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"human-intervention\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"B60205\\\"}],\\\"number\\\":2574,\\\"title\\\":\\\"[Automation] java run fails for xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T10:32:48Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574\\\"}\\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/3698.json:1:{\\\"assignees\\\":[],\\\"author\\\":{\\\"is_bot\\\":true,\\\"login\\\":\\\"app/github-actions\\\"},\\\"body\\\":\\\"### Full Maven coordinates\\\\n\\\\norg.antlr:antlr:3.5.2\\\\n\\\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\\",\\\"comments\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBC5Zqw\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed for `org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2`.\\\\n\\\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3698-library-new-request-org.antlr-antlr-3.5.2-ed6b29a0\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/validation. The run did produce transient work to improve dynamic-access coverage for `org.antlr.tool.GrammarReport` and the generated coverage report reached `11/12` calls covered (`91.67%`), but that work did not persist into the preserved branch: `tests/src/org.antlr/antlr/3.5.2/src/test/java/org_antlr/antlr/AntlrTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, and `stats/org.antlr/antlr/3.5.2/execution-metrics.json` reports `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`.\\\\n\\\\nThe validation logs show the generated tests were also unstable. The first two Gradle runs failed in `GrammarReportTest.toStringDecodesNotifyDataIntoReadableReport()` with `java.util.NoSuchElementException` from `org.antlr.tool.GrammarReport.decodeReportData(...)`, and the later native run failed in `GrammarReportTest.toNotifyStringSerializesGrammarReportData()` with `ANTLR ErrorManager panic` because `org/antlr/tool/templates/messages/languages/en.stg` was not available in the native image. The native trace verification then surfaced a separate missing resource registration for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T01-18-33-718117Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T01-18-33-792466Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T01-19-14-715333Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T01-19-54-174462Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T01-20-36-290771Z.log`\\\\n- `tests/src/org.antlr/antlr/3.5.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Recover or recreate the transient `GrammarReportTest` from the generation log and replace the scaffold-only `AntlrTest`.\\\\n2. Fix the native resource coverage required by the test, especially ANTLR message resources under `org/antlr/tool/templates/messages/languages/`, and confirm whether the `PostDiscoveryFilter` service resource issue is trace-only or also affects the final native test.\\\\n3. Re-run the library JVM/native test flow and preserve the resulting test sources so the branch contains the real generated test instead of the scaffold.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T01:22:14Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3698#issuecomment-4365113771\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEe7rQ\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3698-library-new-request-org.antlr-antlr-3.5.2-0dabca31\\\\n\\\\nThe strongest local evidence suggests the failure happened before or during test generation / coordinate resolution, not during a completed Gradle test run. There are no matching run logs, no pending scratch metrics, and no Gradle `build/` output or dynamic-access report for this issue. The only generated artifacts present are for `org.antlr:antlr-runtime:3.5.2`, not `org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2`: `stats/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/execution-metrics.json` records `status: success` for `org.antlr:antlr-runtime:3.5.2`, and the repo already contains matching generated files at `metadata/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/reachability-metadata.json` and `tests/src/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/src/test/java/org_antlr/antlr_runtime/RemoteDebugEventSocketListenerTest.java`. The preserved branch also has no diff from the current default branch in this worktree, so there is no branch-only WIP to salvage.\\\\n\\\\nPaths a maintainer should inspect:\\\\n- `stats/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/execution-metrics.json`\\\\n- `stats/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/stats.json`\\\\n- `tests/src/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/`\\\\n- `metadata/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/`\\\\n- `forge/script_run_metrics/` and `forge/benchmark_run_metrics/` (no matching run logs found)\\\\n- `tests/src/org.antlr/antlr-runtime/3.5.2/build/` (missing, so no Gradle report/output was preserved)\\\\n\\\\n- Verify whether issue `#3698` should target `org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2` or `org.antlr:antlr-runtime:3.5.2`; the surviving artifacts only support the latter.\\\\n- If `org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2` is the real target, rerun generation for that exact coordinate and capture the first Forge/Gradle failure logs.\\\\n- If the intended target was `org.antlr:antlr-runtime:3.5.2`, close this as stale/duplicate and point maintainers to the already-generated support.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T17:45:01Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3698#issuecomment-4366777261\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true}],\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-30T14:14:22Z\\\",\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPViRdw\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"library-new-request\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Request for supporting a new library, or updating the existing one.\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"83ff2c\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"human-intervention\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"B60205\\\"}],\\\"number\\\":3698,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Support for org.antlr:antlr:3.5.2\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T17:45:06Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3698\\\"}\\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/1292.json:1:{\\\"assignees\\\":[],\\\"author\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MjcwMzI1\\\",\\\"is_bot\\\":false,\\\"login\\\":\\\"graalvmbot\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"graalvm bot\\\"},\\\"body\\\":\\\"## java run on ubuntu-latest / JDK 25\\\\n\\\\nFailure kind: java run\\\\nOS: ubuntu-latest\\\\nJDK: 25\\\\nReproducer: `GVM_TCK_LV=\\\\\\\"1.5.30\\\