g/regression in the HTTP client/server paths rather than a metadata file syntax issue. Dynamic-access coverage and metrics were not produced.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect `logs/io.netty:netty-common:4.2.1.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`, `logs/io.netty:netty-common:4.2.1.Final/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_918.log`, and `tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.115.Final/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`.\\\\n\\\\nNext steps:\\\\n1. Verify whether reusing the `4.1.115.Final` Netty test project for `4.2.1.Final` is valid; if not, scaffold or adapt a dedicated `tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.2.1.Final` test project.\\\\n2. Reproduce the failing native test locally and debug the stalled `noSsl()`, `withAdaptive()`, and `withSsl()` paths, focusing on the reported deadlock/parked-thread behavior.\\\\n3. Reassess `metadata/io.netty/netty-common/4.2.1.Final/reachability-metadata.json` only after the test scaffold/runtime mismatch is ruled out, since the current evidence points to a native runtime hang.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T11:10:56Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/918#issuecomment-4366025114\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true}],\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-01-08T15:17:47Z\\\",\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"library-unsupported-version\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"bb366d\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0ftA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"fails-native-image-run\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Tests fail in native execution\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"d93f0b\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"human-intervention\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-acces