th Gradle 10.\\\\n\\\\nYou can use '--warning-mode all' to show the individual deprecation warnings and determine if they come from your own scripts or plugins.\\\\n\\\\nFor more on this, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\\\n10 actionable tasks: 2 executed, 8 up-to-date\\\\nThere were failing tests. See the report at: file:///home/runner/work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.0.b2/build/reports/tests/test/index.html\\\\n\\\\n* Try:\\\\n> Run with --scan to generate a Build Scan (Powered by Develocity).\\\\n\\\\nBUILD FAILED in 2s\\\\n\\\\n> Task :javaTest FAILED\\\\n\\\\n[Incubating] Problems report is available at: file:///home/runner/work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/graalvm-reachability-metadata/build/reports/problems/problems-report.html\\\\n\\\\nFAILURE: Build failed with an exception.\\\\n\\\\n* What went wrong:\\\\nExecution failed for task ':javaTest'.\\\\n> Java tests failed\\\\n\\\\n* Try:\\\\n> Run with --stacktrace option to get the stack trace.\\\\n> Run with --info or --debug option to get more log output.\\\\n> Run with --scan to generate a Build Scan (Powered by Develocity).\\\\n> Get more help at https://help.gradle.org.\\\\n\\\\nDeprecated Gradle features were used in this build, making it incompatible with Gradle 10.\\\\n\\\\nYou can use '--warning-mode all' to show the individual deprecation warnings and determine if they come from your own scripts or plugins.\\\\n\\\\nFor more on this, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\\\n\\\\nBUILD FAILED in 4s\\\\n11 actionable tasks: 3 executed, 8 up-to-date\\\\n❌ ERROR: 'java run' for 1.2.01 failed with exit code 1.\\\\nFAILED[java run][1.2.01][GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=\\\\\\\"future-defaults-all\\\\\\\" GVM_TCK_LV=\\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\" ./gradlew clean javaTest -Pcoordinates=\\\\\\\"xml-apis:xml-apis:1.0.b2\\\\\\\"]\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\",\\\"comments\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAjjYaA\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01` with workflow status `failure`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-8fda82cb\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the initial Java runtime test reproduction/fix stage (`test`/`javaTest`). Concrete evidence: no matching run logs were preserved, run metrics and dynamic-access coverage are unavailable, the preserved branch was created from `HEAD` and pushed with no additional commit, and there is no generated `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/`, `metadata/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/`, or `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/` tree in the preserved worktree. This suggests the job failed before it produced any recoverable `1.2.01` artifacts.\\\\n\\\\nPaths to inspect:\\\\n- `forge_run_metrics/2574-1506b5af/logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/` (expected workflow logs; not present in the scratch metrics repo)\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/` (expected copied logs on the preserved branch; not present)\\\\n- `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/build/test-results/test/` and `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/build/reports/tests/test/` after reproducing locally\\\\n\\\\nNext steps:\\\\n1. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01 --stacktrace` to capture the first runtime failure.\\\\n2. If the `1.2.01` test scaffold is still missing, compare against `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.0.b2/` and decide whether a concrete runtime test needs to be added or adapted before retrying.\\\\n3. Preserve the Gradle output under `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/` or attach it to this issue, then continue the version-bump fix manually.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T03:56:19Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4332247144\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAmt9IQ\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-d0044eeb\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was after the JVM test repair, during stats/coverage collection for this coordinate. In `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T13-12-31-752286Z.log`, the original `fails-java-run` error is a stale assertion in `Xml_apisTest.versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` (`actual \\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\"` vs expected `\\\\\\\"1.0\\\\\\\"` at `Xml_apisTest.java:74`), and the same log later shows the test was updated and `./gradlew test` passed with `10 tests successful, 0 failed`. However, the run metrics still report `Generated LOC: 0` and the starting and ending commit both as `ea6ee71c8d9d6d854442ef0d9cad8a0036e43096`, so that validated fix was not recorded. The stronger blocker appears in `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/906df4c8d954eba5a3a9da7b1ae10ee3.out`, where `:jacocoTestReport` fails with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`; this matches `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, which found that Maven Central exposes only the `1.2.01` POM and that it relocates to `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2`. Dynamic-access coverage being unavailable is consistent with that failure.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T13-12-31-752286Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/0f4a273c0380b8e49ad51ab05a8a08b1.out`, and `build/tests/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/906df4c8d954eba5a3a9da7b1ae10ee3.out`.\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Recreate or restore the `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01` test project and reapply the one-line assertion fix so `Version.getVersionNum()` expects `1.2.01`, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`.\\\\n2. Decide how stats/coverage should handle this relocated, POM-only coordinate: either point the workflow at the actual jar artifact or explicitly treat JaCoCo/dynamic-access coverage as unavailable for this case.\\\\n3. Rerun the stats/coverage lane after that adjustment and verify whether coverage can be generated or must remain unavailable by design.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T13:14:30Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4335566113\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBCHHbA\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`.\\\\n\\\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-4a91c442\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the `fix-java-run-fail` generation/orchestration step after the original JVM failure was reproduced. The raw Gradle log at `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-42-48-440922Z.log` shows the real failure: `Xml_apisTest > versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` failed because actual `\\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\"` did not contain expected `\\\\\\\"1.0\\\\\\\"` at `Xml_apisTest.java:74`. After that, `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T16-43-43-207622Z.log` shows the automation struggling with source-context resolution (`find: ‘local_repositories/source_context/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/main’: No such file or directory`), and `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, with the same starting and ending commit (`af4b76c33bf1b9d99f5100e78e9751f3911cbe0b`).\\\\n\\\\nLater retries do not show a persistent library/runtime failure: `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-43-43-219421Z.log` and `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-49-43-666186Z.log` both report `versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` and all 10 tests passing. There is also a separate metadata detour in `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/metadata-fix/codex.log`, which does not match the original assertion-based `fails-java-run` problem. Dynamic-access coverage is unavailable for this run.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-42-48-440922Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T16-43-43-207622Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-43-43-219421Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\\\n- `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/execution-metrics.json`\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Recreate the original JVM failure and verify whether `versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` should assert `1.2.01` (or a broader `1.2`-series value) instead of `1.0`.\\\\n2. Ignore the metadata-fix detour unless a clean rerun proves `metadata/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/reachability-metadata.json` is actually required.\\\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01` from a clean worktree, then regenerate stats if needed so the final fix and coverage are captured cleanly.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-02T16:53:30Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4364289900\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDs84w\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job for `xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2574-fails-java-run-xml-apis-xml-apis-1.2.01-7a34b9b0\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the Java test repair step. In `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-22-51-489745Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T10-23-47-354915Z.log`, `Xml_apisTest.versionClassReportsXmlCommonsIdentity()` fails because `Version.getVersionNum()` returns `\\\\\\\"1.2.01\\\\\\\"` but the generated test still asserts that it should contain `\\\\\\\"1.0\\\\\\\"` (`Xml_apisTest.java:74`). The metrics confirm automation never turned that into a usable fix: `stats/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, identical start/end commits, and no recorded test or metadata artifact.\\\\n\\\\nThere was also a secondary failure during trace verification. `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T10-24-17-910503Z.log` aborts with `IllegalArgumentException: Option TraceMetadataConditionPackages must contain package prefixes separated by ','`, which suggests the trace run used `xml-apis` instead of valid Java package prefixes. Later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-23-47-360518Z.log` and `.../gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-29-49-644665Z.log` reached `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, but that success was not captured as a usable automation result.\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Restore or regenerate the `tests/src/xml-apis/xml-apis/1.2.01` test project and update the version assertion to match `1.2.01` behavior instead of the old `1.0` expectation.\\\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01`; if metadata tracing is needed, use valid package prefixes such as `javax.xml,org.apache.xmlcommons,org.w3c.dom,org.xml.sax`.\\\\n3. If the rerun passes, commit the regenerated test/metadata/stats outputs, since the preserved branch only records the failed automation state.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T10:32:43Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574#issuecomment-4365958371\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true}],\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T01:33:30Z\\\",\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"library-unsupported-version\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"bb366d\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0olA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"fails-java-run\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Tests fail during java testing\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"8f51c9\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"human-intervention\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"B60205\\\"}],\\\"number\\\":2574,\\\"title\\\":\\\"[Automation] java run fails for xml-apis:xml-apis:1.2.01\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T10:32:48Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2574\\\"}\\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/424.json:1:{\\\"assignees\\\":[],\\\"author\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"MDQ6VXNlcjg0MTk0OTE=\\\",\\\"is_bot\\\":false,\\\"login\\\":\\\"wetted\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dean Wette\\\"},\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\\\\r\\\\nA clear and concise description of what the problem is. Ex. I'm always frustrated when [...]\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThe graalvm-reachability-metadata supports `org.flywaydb 9.0.1`, but is broken for flyway 10.0.0\\\\r\\\\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/master/metadata/org.flywaydb/flyway-core\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\\\\r\\\\nA clear and concise description of what you want to happen.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n- add support for `org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0`\\\\r\\\\n- add support for `org.flywaydb:flyway-sqlserver:10.0.0`\\\\r\\\\n- add support for `org.flywaydb:flyway-database-oracle:10.0.0`\\\\r\\\\n- add support for `org.flywaydb:flyway-database-postgresql:10.0.0`\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\\\\r\\\\nA clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n- null\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Additional context**\\\\r\\\\nAdd any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n`  | Caused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: The program tried to reflectively invoke method public java.lang.String org.flywaydb.core.internal.command.clean.CleanModeConfigurationExtension.getNamespace() without it being registered for runtime reflection. Add public java.lang.String org.flywaydb.core.internal.command.clean.CleanModeConfigurationExtension.getNamespace() to the reflection metadata to solve this problem. See https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/#reflection for help. |  \\\\r\\\\n`\\\\r\\\\nhttps://github.com/micronaut-projects/micronaut-flyway/actions/runs/6935025730/job/18864351069?pr=472\\\\r\\\\n\\\",\\\"comments\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6KUTPJ\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mhalbritter\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"COLLABORATOR\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Flyway fails with Spring Boot 3.4.0-M2 which uses Flyway `10.17.1`:\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```\\\\r\\\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: The program tried to reflectively invoke method public boolean org.flywaydb.core.internal.publishing.PublishingConfigurationExtension.isPublishResult() without it being registered for runtime reflection. Add public boolean org.flywaydb.core.internal.publishing.PublishingConfigurationExtension.isPublishResult() to the reflection metadata to solve this problem. See https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/#reflection for help.\\\\r\\\\nat org.graalvm.nativeimage.builder/com.oracle.svm.core.reflect.MissingReflectionRegistrationUtils.forQueriedOnlyExecutable(MissingReflectionRegistrationUtils.java:72)\\\\r\\\\nat java.base@21.0.3/java.lang.reflect.Method.acquireMethodAccessor(Method.java:77)\\\\r\\\\n```\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-08-30T09:06:49Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":true,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2320577481\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6KzSNS\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mhalbritter\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"COLLABORATOR\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"I've added metadata for Flyway 10.17.1 in #531.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-09-04T11:33:54Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2328699730\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6WRIJK\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"asm0dey\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"NONE\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"With `10.20.1` and spring `3.4.0` it fails with \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```\\\\r\\\\nThe program tried to reflectively invoke method\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n   public java.lang.String org.flywaydb.core.internal.configuration.extensions.DeployScriptFilenameConfigurationExtension.getScriptFilename()\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n without it being registered for runtime reflection.\\\\r\\\\n```\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-12-05T18:01:01Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2521072202\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6WV7XR\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mhalbritter\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"COLLABORATOR\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"This can be fixed by using the latest version of the reachability metadata:\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```gradle\\\\r\\\\ngraalvmNative {\\\\r\\\\n\\\\tmetadataRepository {\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t\\\\tversion = '0.3.15'\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t}\\\\r\\\\n}\\\\r\\\\n```\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nor\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```xml\\\\r\\\\n<plugin>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t<groupId>org.graalvm.buildtools</groupId>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t<artifactId>native-maven-plugin</artifactId>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t<configuration>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t\\\\t<metadataRepository>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t\\\\t\\\\t<version>0.3.15</version>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t\\\\t</metadataRepository>\\\\r\\\\n\\\\t</configuration>\\\\r\\\\n</plugin>\\\\r\\\\n```\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-12-06T07:29:20Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":true,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[{\\\"content\\\":\\\"THUMBS_UP\\\",\\\"users\\\":{\\\"totalCount\\\":2}}],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2522330577\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6YhBwp\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"msosa\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"NONE\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Upgrading to Spring Boot 3.4.1 did not seem to fix it for me. The location of my error seems a little different than the others I see here though:\\\\r\\\\n```\\\\r\\\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: The program tried to reflectively invoke method public boolean org.flywaydb.core.internal.publishing.PublishingConfigurationExtension.isCheckDriftOnMigrate() without it being registered for runtime reflection.\\\\r\\\\n```\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-12-23T02:42:43Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2558794793\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6ZgBOW\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mhalbritter\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"COLLABORATOR\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"> Spring Boot 3.4.1 will use the latest Native Build Tools release, which includes this reachability metadata version by default.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThis isn't true, sorry!\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nSpring Boot 3.4.1 uses Native Build Tools [0.10.4](https://github.com/graalvm/native-build-tools/releases/tag/0.10.4), which uses the [0.3.14 metadata](https://github.com/graalvm/native-build-tools/pull/640/files#diff-697f70cdd88ba88fe77eebda60c7e143f6ad1286bca75017421e93ad84fb87dfR4).\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nSo the workaround from https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2522330577 still applies to Spring Boot 3.4.1.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2025-01-07T13:33:28Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2575307670\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc6ZmimI\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"goafabric\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"NONE\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"I am having the same problem since boot 3.4x with PublishingConfigurationExtension,\\\\r\\\\nand also since 3.3 there is a similar problem with \\\\\\\"TransactionalModel\\\\\\\" if flyway is combined with Hibernate.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThe following Spring annotations would fix it, i think this could be easily translated to graalvm defaults.\\\\r\\\\nAnd I understand the workaround that Moritz mentioned concerning the first issue.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```java\\\\r\\\\n@RegisterReflection(classes = {org.flywaydb.core.internal.publishing.PublishingConfigurationExtension.class, org.flywaydb.database.postgresql.TransactionalModel.class}, memberCategories = {MemberCategory.INVOKE_PUBLIC_METHODS, MemberCategory.INVOKE_PUBLIC_CONSTRUCTORS})\\\\r\\\\n```\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2025-01-08T08:15:29Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":true,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-2577017224\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc601e9f\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"joshlong\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"NONE\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"has this been fixed in the later versions of Spring Boot? \\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2025-07-03T23:15:36Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-3033919327\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc603mVm\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"goafabric\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"NONE\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"@joshlong \\\\nNope, just verified with Boot 3.5.3 and buildtools.native 0.10.6\\\\nWhen removing the hints i mentioned previously it will still crash\\\\n\\\\nCaused by: org.flywaydb.core.api.FlywayException: No serializer found for class org.flywaydb.database.postgresql.TransactionalModel and no properties discovered to create BeanSerializer (to avoid exception, disable SerializationFeature.FAIL_ON_EMPTY_BEANS). This appears to be a native image, in which case you may need to configure reflection for the class that is to be serialized (through reference chain: org.flywaydb.database.postgresql.PostgreSQLConfigurationExtension[\\\\\\\"transactional\\\\\\\"])\\\\n\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2025-07-04T04:38:42Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-3034473830\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc604QPs\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"wilkinsona\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"CONTRIBUTOR\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"[`PublishingConfigurationExtensions`](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/af522f7517534f3c0df9e7169f50bee419f8c3f5/metadata/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.20.1/reflect-config.json#L202-L246) is covered in recent versions of the metadata so I think things are OK from a `flyway-core` perspective. Boot's Flyway smoke test [suggests that's the case too](https://spring-asa-aot-smoke-tests-dashboard.azuremicroservices.io/#boot). It sounds like some metadata for `flyway-database-postgresql` is still needed though as `org.flywaydb.database.postgresql.TransactionalModel` isn't covered by the metadata.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2025-07-04T06:05:37Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-3034645484\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc604yQ9\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"wilkinsona\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"CONTRIBUTOR\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"~@goafabric could you please share a minimal Boot app that fails with Flyway and PostgreSQL? A minimal smoke test doesn't fail for me.~\\\\n\\\\nIt only fails if you're configured `spring.flyway.postgresql.transactional-lock`. That results in `PostgreSQLConfigurationExtension` having a non-null `org.flywaydb.database.postgresql.TransactionalModel`.\\\\n\\\\nI've opened https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/648.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2025-07-04T07:14:12Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":true,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-3034784829\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBCymkA\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"### Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed for `org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0`.\\\\n\\\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-424-library-new-request-org.flywaydb-flyway-core-10.0.0-769da1bd\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/result capture, not library validation itself. In `stats/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/execution-metrics.json`, the run is recorded as `status: failure` with `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`. The preserved branch still contains only the scaffold test `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/src/test/java/org_flywaydb/flyway_core/Flyway_coreTest.java`, which still prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`, and the Gradle log shows that placeholder test is what actually ran successfully.\\\\n\\\\nThe generation transcript shows the agent did draft a real `ClassUtilsTest.java` and reported it as an untracked file, but that file was never preserved into the branch, so the generated test work was effectively lost. See `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T00-06-07-548504Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T00-06-07-557280Z.log`, and `stats/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/execution-metrics.json`. There was also a later downstream native verification failure: `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T00-06-57-420040Z.log` shows `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`. The reported dynamic-access coverage is only 18/40 (45.00%), which is below the 50% floor for a `library-new-request`.\\\\n\\\\nRecommended manual next steps:\\\\n1. Recover or recreate the intended library-specific Flyway tests from the generation transcript and commit them under `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/`, replacing the scaffold placeholder.\\\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0` and confirm dynamic-access coverage improves past 50%.\\\\n3. If native verification still fails, add the missing resource registration for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter` and rerun native trace verification.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T00:08:53Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-4365002384\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDPmHg\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job for `org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-424-library-new-request-org.flywaydb-flyway-core-10.0.0-2f3aa381\\\\n\\\\nMost likely failure stage: `add-new-library-support` / test-generation persistence. The preserved tree still contains only the placeholder test at `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/src/test/java/org_flywaydb/flyway_core/Flyway_coreTest.java`, while `stats/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/execution-metrics.json` reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, `artifacts.metadata_file: None`, and the starting/ending commit are identical. At the same time, the generation log shows a proposed `ClassUtilsTest`, and the build outputs prove that transient test actually ran: `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_flywaydb.flyway_core.ClassUtilsTest.xml` has 9 passing tests, and `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows `ClassUtils` reached `18/18`, but overall dynamic-access coverage is only `18/40` (45%), below the new-library 50% gate.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T05-31-30-594746Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T05-31-30-604905Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T05-32-08-371023Z.log`\\\\n\\\\nManual next steps:\\\\n1. Recover the generated `ClassUtilsTest` from the generation log/build outputs into `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/src/test/java/...` and replace the placeholder `Flyway_coreTest`.\\\\n2. Extend the tests to cover at least one additional uncovered path beyond `ClassUtils` (for example `ClassicConfiguration`, `MergeUtils`, or the resource-loading paths) so dynamic-access coverage exceeds 50%.\\\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0` and confirm the updated result in `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T05:33:47Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-4365477406\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDgBDw\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed for `org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-424-library-update-request-org.flywaydb-flyway-core-10.0.0-f785464e\\\\n\\\\nMost likely failing stage: generated test execution during `gradle-test` / `:nativeTest`. In `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T05-31-30-604905Z.log`, the generated `org_flywaydb.flyway_core.ClassUtilsTest` runs under Native Image and `instantiatesClassByNameWithExpressionConstructorPath()` fails with `org.flywaydb.core.api.FlywayException: Unable to instantiate class org_flywaydb.flyway_core.ClassUtilsTest$DefaultConstructible`, caused by `java.lang.NoSuchMethodException: <unbound>=Class.new();`. That log ends with `9 tests successful`, `1 tests failed`, and `BUILD FAILED`. The trace-image build itself succeeds in `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T05-32-08-371023Z.log`, so this looks like a bad generated test rather than a native-image build failure.\\\\n\\\\nThere is also a persistence inconsistency worth checking. `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T05-31-30-594746Z.log` shows the generator proposing a new `ClassUtilsTest`, but `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_424.log` records that the preserved tree still only had the placeholder `Flyway_coreTest`, with `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`. That suggests the generated test either was not persisted cleanly or was discarded after the failing run.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T05-31-30-604905Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T05-31-30-594746Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T05-32-08-371023Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_424.log`\\\\n\\\\n1. Recover or recreate `ClassUtilsTest` in `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/src/test/java/...` so the preserved branch contains the actual generated test instead of only the placeholder scaffold.\\\\n2. Fix or remove `instantiatesClassByNameWithExpressionConstructorPath()` so it matches `ClassUtils.instantiate` behavior, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0`.\\\\n3. After the test passes, re-check dynamic-access coverage and add coverage beyond `ClassUtils` if needed before resuming automation.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T08:24:48Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424#issuecomment-4365746447\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true}],\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2023-11-21T15:08:28Z\\\",\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc7_VUq2\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"priority\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"This is a priority issue\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ffffff\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPVjvyQ\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"library-update-request\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The current metadata for a library does not work for the user.\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"593691\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"human-intervention\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"B60205\\\"}],\\\"number\\\":424,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Update existing library: org.flywaydb:flyway-core:10.0.0\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-03T08:24:54Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/424\\\"}\\n/tmp/rhei-issue-details/3645.json:1:{\\\"assignees\\\":[],\\\"author\\\":{\\\"is_bot\\\":true,\\\"login\\\":\\\"app/github-actions\\\"},\\\"body\\\":\\\"### Full Maven coordinates\\\\n\\\\nnet.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6\\\\n\\\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\\",\\\"comments\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABA-fPsg\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed for `net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6`. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3645-library-ne