kflow for `org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1` with verbose logging and capture the first exception before metrics writing.\\\\n- Manually scaffold `tests/src/org.opengauss/opengauss-jdbc/3.1.1` from `3.1.0-og` and run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1` to reproduce the real Java runtime failure.\\\\n- If it crashes before `./gradlew test` again, inspect the setup path in `ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py`, especially project preparation, source-context preparation, and metrics writing for this library.\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-27T19:13:10Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/719#issuecomment-4329754032\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABAjeWJQ\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed for `org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-719-fails-java-run-org.opengauss-opengauss-jdbc-3.1.1-8a3f9c44\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the `fails-java-run` repair lane. The generated `PGXAConnectionTest` did not compile because `XAConnection` was used in try-with-resources even though it is not `AutoCloseable` (`PGXAConnectionTest.java:77`), and after that was adjusted a later JVM run still failed in `SingleCertValidatingFactoryTest.loadsPinnedServerCertificateFromClasspathResource()` with `java.security.cert.CertificateException: Could not parse certificate: java.io.IOException: Stream closed`. Metrics also indicate that no durable fix was exported: `Generated LOC: 0`, start commit `7d81085976797f718352d79cc6acade7fcddf7df`, end commit `7d81085976797f718352d79cc6acade7fcddf7df`, and dynamic-access coverage was unavailable.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T02-54-40-669505Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T02-45-33-173275Z.log`\\\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\\\n- `post-gen-interventions/org.opengauss_opengauss-jdbc_3.1.1.md`\\\\n\\\\nNext steps:\\\\n1. Fix or replace the generated `PGXAConnectionTest` so `tests/src/org.opengauss/opengauss-jdbc/3.1.1` compiles cleanly, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1`.\\\\n2. Investigate `SingleCertValidatingFactoryTest` resource loading so the certificate stream stays valid while `SingleCertValidatingFactory` parses it.\\\\n3. If the JVM lane passes, rerun native/metadata validation and review the native blockers already documented in `metadata-fix/codex.log` / the post-gen report (`BaseDataSourceTest`, `EscapedFunctionsTest`, and the Bouncy Castle provider path).\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-28T03:30:14Z\\\",\\\"includesCreatedEdit\\\":false,\\\"isMinimized\\\":false,\\\"minimizedReason\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"reactionGroups\\\":[],\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/719#issuecomment-4332164645\\\",\\\"viewerDidAuthor\\\":true},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBDwlQQ\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"vjovanov\\\"},\\\"authorAssociation\\\":\\\"MEMBER\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Human intervention needed\\\\n\\\\nThe automated job failed for `org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1`. Preserved work/logs are available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-719-fails-java-run-org.opengauss-opengauss-jdbc-3.1.1-aa99f1d3\\\\n\\\\nThe most likely failing stage was the `fix-java-run-fail` JVM test reproduction/fix step, not native-image verification. `stats/org.opengauss/opengauss-jdbc/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json` ended with `status: failure`, only `2` iterations, `generated_loc: 0`, identical starting/ending commits (`3f6877c335cfba994dff8491c507c202a0f5c4e1`), and dynamic-access coverage unavailable, so the job never produced a candidate fix. The JVM test failed in `Opengauss_jdbcTest.beforeAll`: `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-59-29-910659Z.log` shows `beforeAll() timed out after 60 seconds` in `Awaitility` at `Opengauss_jdbcTest.java:56`, and `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T11-03-03-353721Z.log` shows the rerun reaching the connection attempt but failing with `org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: The connection attempt failed`, caused by `java.io.EOFException` during authentication from `openConnection` at `Opengauss_jdbcTest.java:47` / `beforeAll` line 64. The generation log also shows the expected source-context path `local_repositories/source_context/org.opengauss/opengauss-jdbc/3.1.1/main` was missing, which likely contributed to the zero-LOC outcome. For contrast, `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T11-04-27-131077Z.log` ended with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, so the blocker is the Java test setup/connection path.\\\\n\\\\nPlease inspect:\\\\n- `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T10-59-29-910659Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T11-03-03-353721Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T11-03-03-344629Z.log`\\\\n- `logs/org.opengauss:opengauss-jdbc:3.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T11-04-27-131077Z.log`\\\\n\\\\nNext steps:\\\\n1. Manually review/update `Opengauss_jdbcTest.beforeAll` for `3.1.1`, especially the container readiness wait and the first JDBC connection/a